    title: 'iter 226 (autonomous-loop iter 289): stake-valuation parity two-part hypothesis test — BOTH hypotheses BUSTED, iter 227 deeper forensics queued. RESEARCH iter, no production code touched (the StakeInfo decoder already exposes entry.emissionAlpha + entry.alphaEmissionAlpha at lib/freeRpc.js:202-203 — getColdkeyStakeAlpha just doesn\'t sum them, so hypothesis (h) is testable inline by re-aggregating the existing decode). New scripts/probe-stake-hypothesis-test.mjs runs (g) block-sensitivity sweep at target ± [-100,-5,-1,0,+1,+5,+100] blocks around the Jai mantat iter 224-aligned anchor block #8294725, then (h) re-aggregates entries at the same target blockHash with 4 alpha variants — rawStake (current), stakePlusEmission, stakePlusAlphaEmission, stakePlusBoth — computing Σ(α × price) for each against the unchanged per-subnet AMM prices. (g) BLOCK-SENSITIVITY RESULT — RULED OUT: ±5 block window range = 0.000038 τ (0.038 mτ) vs residual 16.197 mτ — three orders of magnitude smaller. ±100 block range (~21 min) = 0.004166 τ (4.166 mτ) — still 4× too small. To explain 16.197 mτ via block-time skew alone would require >400 blocks (~83 min) of separation, vastly outside normal alignment noise. Σα is constant across the entire ±5 block window (stake quantum unchanged), so the small price drift comes purely from AMM pool reserve evolution at the per-block tick. Hypothesis (g) decisively insufficient. (h) EMISSION-INCLUSIVE RESULT — RULED OUT WRONG-DIRECTION: rawStake (current composer) drift = +0.016197 τ; stakePlusEmission drift = +1.078069 τ (66× WIDER); stakePlusAlphaEmission drift = +0.016197 τ (no change — alphaEmissionAlpha is 0.0 on every entry at this block, field unpopulated for delegators in current Bittensor runtime); stakePlusBoth drift = +1.078069 τ. The wrong-direction is itself decisive evidence: Taostats balance_staked is SMALLER than archive raw stake, not larger. Adding any pending-emission component widens the gap. Amending the composer to sum stake+emission would WORSEN parity by 66×. Per-subnet pending emission (top by emissionAlpha + alphaEmissionAlpha): sn62 stakeα=20.04 emα=6.15 (largest pending, 0.105τ at 0.017 price); sn44 stakeα=19.9 emα=2.51 (0.109τ at 0.043 price); sn4 stakeα=20.3 emα=2.49 (0.140τ at 0.056 price). Aggregate emission across all subnets = 1.078 τ — substantial real pending emission that Taostats simply does NOT include in balance_staked. SEARCH-DIRECTION FLIP: the fact that Taostats is SMALLER than archive (rather than larger) flips the search direction for iter 227. New hypotheses surfaced: (i) Taostats applies a validator/delegator haircut (commission, slashing reserve, withhold) before summing — would yield consistent percentage shortfall; (j) Taostats uses an earlier-in-day block (e.g., 00:00Z instead of 23:59:48Z) for per-subnet pricing — to explain 16 mτ over ~24h requires ~0.13% average AMM price drift across the stake-weighted basket, plausible; (k) Taostats excludes a subnet category — e.g., registered hotkeys only, or non-root with sn0 baseline subtraction; (l) Taostats sums at different alpha-share quantum — e.g., uses SubtensorModule.Alpha storage map (per-subnet aggregated) rather than StakeInfoRuntimeApi (per-hotkey). DECISION: (c) HOLD on flag-flip persists. Iter 227 cannot graduate without identifying the +16 mτ source. Iter 227 plan: test (j) first — fetch Taostats /api/dtao/pool/history for a representative subnet (sn64 — largest stakeτ contribution at +1.42 τ) for snapshot day; sample prices at 00:00 / 06:00 / 12:00 / 18:00 / 23:59 UTC. Compute Σ(stakeα × price) at each price snapshot vs archive Σ(stakeα × price) at EOD block. If 16 mτ residual closes when using early-day price snapshot, (j) is confirmed and composer adjusts to use TWAP or early-day pricing. If (j) negative, probe Taostats /api/dtao/coldkey/positions history endpoints for per-position data at snapshot day — tests (k) + (l). Two-file change: scripts/probe-stake-hypothesis-test.mjs (new local-runnable probe with (g) sweep + (h) 4-variant decode + per-subnet pending-emission breakdown + JSON stdout dump) + docs/stake-parity-iter-226.md (full (g) sweep table + (h) 4-variant comparison + per-subnet emission breakdown + 8-hypothesis verdict matrix + (i/j/k/l) new-direction writeup + iter 227 plan + 2 lesson candidates). No production code changed. Hypothesis verdict matrix (cumulative after iter 226): (a) AMM block drift RULED OUT (iter 225), (b) rounding asymmetry RULED OUT (iter 225), (c) sn0 convention RULED OUT (iter 225), (d) pending-unbond single subnet UNLIKELY, (e) semantic split RULED OUT-ish (covered by h), (f) integer-division ordering RULED OUT (iter 225), (g) sub-12s block-time skew RULED OUT (iter 226), (h) Taostats includes pending emission RULED OUT (iter 226). Lesson candidates: (1) lessons_taostats_balance_staked_smaller_than_archive.md — Taostats /api/account/history/v1.balance_staked is SMALLER than archive raw-stake Σ(stakeα × price) at the same block, by ~0.1–0.2% on dTAO-era wallets; gap is NOT pending alpha emission (overshoots 66× wrong-sign) and NOT sub-12s block-time skew (±5 block range is 3 orders of magnitude smaller); likely candidates are intraday price snapshot timing, validator/delegator haircut, or position-set filtering; use /api/dtao/stake_balance/latest/v1 for current-block parity (RAO-exact). (2) lessons_stakeinfo_alpha_emission_unpopulated.md — StakeInfoRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey returns per-entry alpha_emission field as 0 for delegator-only coldkeys in current Bittensor runtime (block ~8.3M, Jun 2026); field is decoded but unused in valuation; emission field is populated and represents pending alpha emission (substantial — ~1 τ aggregate on a 12 τ stake), but Taostats balance_staked does NOT include it. Extends iter 219+220+221+222+223+224+225 sequence to iter 226 — Priority #1 starting-balance leg remains in attribution-validated state with HOLD on graduation pending iter 227 deeper forensics.',
