    body: 'Iter 200. PRIMARY shipped — pnlDecomp.verdict PARENT chip. Eighth iter in the surface-symmetry sweep. Discovered during iter 199 pre-ship audit: pnlDecomposition() emits BOTH annualVsApyVerdict (3-label CHILD verdict shipped iter 199 as §3 "Realised vs structural" h3) AND the parent `verdict` field with 7 labels classifying staking-vs-price contribution mix — also has its own verdictReason field, also never rendered to the user. PRE-SHIP AUDIT (per iter 200 fire framing): grepped lib/report.js for `verdict:` near pnlDecomposition() (line 402-487) confirmed producer at lines 438-462 emits 7 labels (stalled / price_headwind / underperforming / yield_driven / windfall / price_tailwind / balanced) with verdictReason at line 485 returned in the payload object (lines 472-486). Payload top-level key `pnlDecomp` at lib/report.js:2839. Grepped lib/ai-insights.js — line 172-175 reads `report.pnlDecomp.verdict` and `.verdictReason` into §0 prompt as "Verdict: {verdict} — {verdictReason}" since iter ~117 (block runs before annualVsApyGapPp/Verdict at lines 188-193). Grepped app/_components/Report.jsx for prior `pnlv-verdict-chip` / `pnldec-verdict-chip` / `pnl-verdict-chip` / `pnlDec.verdict` consumer — none present, only pnlDec.annualVsApyVerdict shipped iter 199 at line 1635. Confirmed unshipped. SHIP (3-file): (A) app/_components/Report.jsx — pnlDec destructure unchanged (iter 199 already added it); new `<h3 className="sub-h pnlv-head-title">Driver of return</h3>` inserted between the .tax-year-panel closing `)}` (line 1121) and the iter 197 sf-head-title comment block (line 1122). Inline `<span className="pnlv-verdict-chip pnlv-verdict-{verdict-with-dashes}">` rendering `· verdict_label` with `title={pnlDec.verdictReason || `PnL decomposition verdict: ${pnlDec.verdict}`}` (fallback in case verdictReason ever drops out of payload). null-guarded by `pnlDec && pnlDec.available && pnlDec.verdict`. Iter 200 comment block above the h3 explains the 7-label set + producer locations + payload key + ai-insights consumer line + tier semantics. (B) app/globals.css — new `.pnlv-verdict-chip` base rule (color var(--dim), 11px tabular-nums, opacity 0.85, font-weight 400, margin-left 2px — matches iter 197/198/199 base) + 1 "quiet" tier rule covering 3 labels (.pnlv-verdict-stalled / .pnlv-verdict-windfall / .pnlv-verdict-price-tailwind → italic 0.7) + 1 "cautionary" tier rule covering 2 labels (.pnlv-verdict-price-headwind / .pnlv-verdict-underperforming → 500-weight 0.95). Two "active" labels (.pnlv-verdict-yield-driven / .pnlv-verdict-balanced) fall through to base 0.85 — these are the healthy steady-state reads, present-but-not-warning context. WHY THIS TIER PARTITION: stalled is the no-signal label (the verdict explicitly notes "momentum has flattened"), windfall and price_tailwind both deliver the "don\'t extrapolate the headline, price did the work" warning whose severity is already owned by §0 narrative — chip presence is context not alarm, hence quiet. price_headwind and underperforming are both yield-or-strategy-not-landing labels worth user eyes: price_headwind says the structural staking IS working but absorbed by price drag, underperforming says structural and price BOTH negative — both deserve the same cautionary weight, not green/red but worth a glance. yield_driven and balanced are the healthy reads — staking is doing its job (yield_driven) or both components are contributing (balanced) — present-but-not-warning, hence base. (C) lib/changelog-entries.js — this entry. NON-CHANGES: lib/report.js unchanged (pnlDecomposition() function, verdict logic, verdictReason strings, and pnlDecomp payload key already shipped iter ~117, no logic change); lib/ai-insights.js unchanged (§0 prompt already reads dec.verdict at line 175); lib/bittensor-kb.js unchanged (KB PNL_DECOMPOSITION section already covers all 7 labels via the iter 117-era ship); iter 194 emit-off-epoch rename held; iter 195 §3 yield-table emission chip held; iter 196 drawdownVerdict chip held; iter 197 sf-verdict-chip held; iter 198 mwd-verdict-chip held; iter 199 aav-verdict-chip held. WHY NEW H3 vs INLINE ON pnl-income-breakdown: option (a) "chip directly next to §2 h2 PnL header" diverges from the iter 195-199 h3 pattern (would put chip at section level not sub-section level); option (b) "chip inline on .pnl-income-breakdown div" cramps the 11px chip against the already-busy "Breakdown · Staking · Price" run; option (c) NEW h3 sub-header BETWEEN tax-year-panel and sf-head-title h3 matches iter 197/198/199 sub-h3 pattern exactly — gives §2 four sub-sections (AU tax-year, Driver of return THIS ITER, Staking flows iter 197+198, Drawdown & recovery iter 196), each with a single explicit verdict label at the header. The "Driver of return" title mirrors the §0 KB PNL_DECOMPOSITION framing verbatim. WHY USE THE PRODUCER\'S verdictReason DIRECTLY vs CLIENT SYNTHESIS: iter 199 annualVsApyVerdict had only 3 labels with deterministic thresholds and producer emitted LABEL only — client synthesis was the smaller diff. iter 200 pnlDecomp.verdict has 7 labels with per-branch verdictReason already emitted from the producer (lines 442/445/448/451/458/461) — using verdictReason verbatim is the smaller diff AND keeps chip vocabulary IDENTICAL to what §0 AI Insights reads. The same "user sees the same threshold the AI sees" pattern as iter 196 ddv chip + iter 197 sfv chip + iter 198 mwd chip. SMOKE TARGET (after deploy): live coldkey URL Jai\'s Subnets `/report/5EKFph3D839fxdbQwhAHyM4CQzBHNpLSecUAteNZKqW1G5cd` per iter 194 verify lesson — §2 should now show "Driver of return · {verdict_label}" h3 between the AU tax-year breakdown panel and the "Staking flows" h3, with className containing `pnlv-verdict-chip pnlv-verdict-{label}` and tooltip = pnlDec.verdictReason (the threshold-citing string from the producer). iter 200 = ROUND MILESTONE — shipped hygienic, no party tag, no special prose, no inflated wording (treated as iter 199 exactly). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~21 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
