    body: 'Iter 198. PRIMARY shipped — multiWindowDurabilityVerdict chip as a SECOND chip on the existing iter 197 .sf-head-title h3. Sixth iter in the surface-symmetry sweep (validatorConcentration iter 192, EMISSION_ALIGNMENT chips iter 193+194+195, drawdownVerdict iter 196, stakingFlowVerdict iter 197, multiWindowDurabilityVerdict iter 198). PRE-SHIP AUDIT (per iter 198 fire framing): grepped lib/report.js for `multiWindowDurabilityVerdict` — producer at line 1295 (signature: `multiWindowDurabilityVerdict({ mwnf, book })`), invocation at line 2716 (consumes mwnf from multiWindowNetFlow + gt.currentPortfolioTao as book), payload attached as sfv sub-property at line 2828 (`sfVerdict.multiWindowDurability = mwDurability;` per iter 138 unconditional-attach fix — multi-window enrichment was previously gated on sfVerdict.available, which kept it invisible on Jai\'s 5Cnz1juP coldkey where FY-windowed gt returns available:false). Grepped app/_components/Report.jsx for any prior `mwd-verdict-chip` or `durability-verdict-chip` or `multiWindowDurability` consumer — none present, confirmed unshipped. Verdict labels (9 with thresholds, all read from producer): (1) dormant_harvest_only — zero transfer events across 365d, "wallet has zero transfer_in/transfer_out events across the trailing 365d — pure root-staking harvest behaviour; validator selection and root staking ARE the strategy, behavioural capital-flow signals do not apply"; (2) flat — all four window net flows within ±1τ; (3) one_off_spike — 30d holds ≥80% of 365d gross flow with gross365 > 1τ; (4) fading_flow — 365d had material flow but last 30d went quiet (count===0 or |net|<0.5 && count≤1) with year material above max(1, 0.5% of book); (5) recent_reversal_to_accumulation — 30d net positive flipped against 365d net negative, both material; (6) recent_reversal_to_distribution — 30d net negative flipped against 365d net positive, both material; (7) sustained_accumulation — all four windows net positive AND |p365.netTao| > matFloor; (8) sustained_distribution — all four windows net negative AND |p365.netTao| > matFloor; (9) mixed — fallthrough, windows split direction. The verdictReason field on each label carries the threshold-citing string verbatim into the chip tooltip — same iter 196+197 pattern where the user sees the same threshold the AI sees. SHIP (3-file): (A) app/_components/Report.jsx — same iter 197 destructure unchanged (`stakingFlowVerdict: sfv` already extracts the parent), added SECOND `<span>` inside the existing `<h3 className="sub-h sf-head-title">` after the sfv chip, null-guarded by `sfv && sfv.multiWindowDurability && sfv.multiWindowDurability.available && sfv.multiWindowDurability.verdict`, renders `· verdict_label` (underscore→space prettyprint) with `title={sfv.multiWindowDurability.verdictReason}`, className `mwd-verdict-chip mwd-verdict-{verdict-with-dashes}`. Iter 198 comment block above the h3 explains the 9-label set + tier semantics + payload location. WHY SECOND CHIP IN SAME H3 (option c from fire framing): option (a) "single chip showing both verdicts" too cluttered; option (b) "new <h3>Flow durability</h3>" claims another h3 sub-section just for a long-arc context-add when §2 already has three h3s (AU tax-year, Staking flows iter 197, Drawdown iter 196). Option (c) gives the user "single-window verdict · long-arc verdict" reading verbatim from the same h3, which mirrors the natural English "currently capitalising, sustained accumulation arc" pattern. (B) app/globals.css — new `.mwd-verdict-chip` base rule (color var(--dim), 11px tabular-nums, opacity 0.85, font-weight 400, margin-left 2px — matches iter 197 base) + 4 "quiet" tier rules (dormant-harvest-only, flat, fading-flow, one-off-spike → italic 0.7) + 2 "cautionary" tier rules (recent-reversal-to-accumulation, recent-reversal-to-distribution → 500-weight 0.95). Three "active" labels (sustained-accumulation, sustained-distribution, mixed) fall through to the base rule at opacity 0.85 — they\'re directional or mixed, neither low-signal nor flip-warning. WHY THIS TIER PARTITION: dormant_harvest_only is intentionally quiet — the verdict explicitly notes "behavioural capital-flow signals do not apply", so the chip\'s presence should not draw attention. flat / fading_flow / one_off_spike are all low-signal labels (no directional information worth narrating). The two reversal labels deserve the cautionary tier because a pattern flip IS the actionable read — "you\'ve been accumulating for a year but the last 30d went distribution" is a regime change worth user eyes. sustained_accumulation and sustained_distribution are persistent-arc reads, useful information but not warning, hence base. mixed is fallthrough — signal exists but doesn\'t parse, base opacity. (C) lib/changelog-entries.js — this entry. NON-CHANGES: lib/report.js unchanged (multiWindowDurabilityVerdict() function and payload key already shipped iter 137/138, no logic change); lib/ai-insights.js unchanged (§0 prompt already reads multiWindowDurability via existing sfv channel); lib/bittensor-kb.js unchanged (KB heuristics for durability arcs already cover all 9 labels via the iter 137-era ship); iter 194 emit-off-epoch rename held; iter 195 §3 yield-table chip held; iter 196 drawdownVerdict chip held; iter 197 sf-verdict-chip held. SMOKE TARGET (after deploy): live coldkey URL Jai\'s Subnets `/report/5EKFph3D839fxdbQwhAHyM4CQzBHNpLSecUAteNZKqW1G5cd` per iter 194 verify lesson — §2 "Staking flows" h3 should now show "Staking flows · {sf_verdict} · {mwd_verdict}" with TWO chips (sf-verdict-chip + mwd-verdict-chip) on the same h3, both with verdictReason tooltips. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~21 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
