    body: 'Iter 197. PRIMARY shipped — stakingFlowVerdict chip. Same surface-symmetry pattern as iter 196 ddv chip, applied to the staking-flow side of §2 PnL. PRE-SHIP AUDIT (per iter 197 fire framing): grepped lib/report.js for `stakingFlowVerdict` — producer at line 1096, payload key at line 2844 (top-level `stakingFlowVerdict` on report data, same shape as drawdownVerdict at line 2843). Grepped app/_components/Report.jsx for any prior `sf-verdict-chip` or `staking-flow-verdict-chip` or `stakingFlowVerdict` consumer — none present, only references to constituent fields (transferInTao/transferOutTao Stats labels at lines 1124-1125). Confirmed unshipped. The 8 verdict labels with their threshold gates (from stakingFlowVerdict()): (1) hands_off — transferCount === 0, "zero transfers in window — wallet untouched, all balance change is price + staking income, do not manufacture a flow narrative"; (2) passive — grossPctOfBook < 0.02, "gross flow X% of book over Yd — sub-threshold, treat as passive holding, don\'t narrate as a flow"; (3) capitalising — absNetPct > 0.15 && netTao > 0 && transferIn > 2 × dailyIncome, "net +X% with transfersIn N× staking income — externally funding the position, not just compounding yield"; (4) accumulation — absNetPct > 0.15 && netTao > 0 (or modest +); (5) harvesting — absNetPct > 0.15 && netTao < 0 && transferOut > dailyIncome && !underwater, "net -X% with transfersOut > staking income against not-underwater book — sensible trim, not distribution"; (6) distribution — absNetPct > 0.15 && netTao < 0 (or modest -); (7) self_funding — dailyIncome > 0 && |netTao| < dailyIncome, "|net| Xτ < daily-income window Yτ — staking income is doing the work, transfers are noise"; (8) rebalancing — absNetPct < 0.02 with transferCount > 0, "near-zero net flow over N txns — rotation/round-trip, not a directional move". The verdictReason field carries the per-label threshold string verbatim into the chip tooltip — same iter 196 pattern where the user sees the same threshold the AI sees. SHIP (3-file): (A) app/_components/Report.jsx line 453 destructure adds `stakingFlowVerdict: sfv` alongside the existing `drawdownVerdict: ddv`; new `<h3 className="sub-h sf-head-title">Staking flows</h3>` inserted at line ~1122 above the existing transfer-in/out Stats grid (preserved verbatim), carrying inline `<span className="sf-verdict-chip sf-verdict-{verdict-with-dashes}">` rendering `· verdict_label` (underscore→space prettyprint) with `title={sfv.verdictReason}`; null-guarded by `sfv && sfv.available && sfv.verdict`; iter 197 comment block above the h3 explains the 8-label set + three-tier semantics. (B) app/globals.css — new `.sf-verdict-chip` base rule (color var(--dim), 11px tabular-nums, opacity 0.85, font-weight 400, margin-left 2px) + 4 "quiet" tier rules (hands-off, passive, rebalancing, self-funding → italic 0.7) + 1 "cautionary" tier rule (distribution → 500-weight 0.95). Three "active" labels (accumulation, capitalising, harvesting) fall through to the base rule and read at base opacity 0.85 — they\'re directional but not cautionary, so the middle tier is the base. NO green/red — §0 narrative owns severity. (C) lib/changelog-entries.js — this entry. NON-CHANGES: lib/report.js unchanged (stakingFlowVerdict() function and payload key already shipped iter 123, no logic change); lib/ai-insights.js unchanged (§0 prompt already reads stakingFlowVerdict via existing channels); lib/bittensor-kb.js unchanged (KB heuristics for flow patterns already cover all 8 labels); EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT verdict tokens unchanged; iter 194 emit-off-epoch rename held; iter 195 §3 yield-table chip held; iter 196 drawdownVerdict chip held. WHY NEW H3 vs INLINE: §2 PnL already has the §2 Drawdown sub-header (`.drawdown-head h3` "Drawdown & recovery") from iter 196 as a precedent for sub-h structure inside the section, so adding a parallel "Staking flows" sub-h above the transfer-in/out Stats grid completes the §2 visual hierarchy — three sub-sections in §2: AU tax-year breakdown (h3, iter 26-ish), Staking flows (h3, this iter), Drawdown & recovery (h3, ddv chip lives here per iter 196). User scanning §2 now sees one explicit verdict label at each sub-section header rather than only at one of them. WHY THREE TIERS vs ITER 196 TWO TIERS: stakingFlowVerdict semantics don\'t cleanly bisect "resilient vs stressful" like drawdownVerdict does. Five of the eight labels (hands_off, passive, rebalancing, self_funding, harvesting) communicate "no signal worth narrating"; three (accumulation, capitalising, harvesting) are directional-but-healthy; only distribution is the one whose surfacing may warrant user attention without context. Three tiers tracks that gradient — quiet/active/cautionary — better than a 7/1 split would. SMOKE TARGET (after deploy): live coldkey URL Jai\'s Subnets `/report/5EKFph3D839fxdbQwhAHyM4CQzBHNpLSecUAteNZKqW1G5cd` per iter 194 verify lesson §2 should now show "Staking flows · {verdict_label}" h3 above the transfer-in/out stats grid, with className containing `sf-verdict-chip sf-verdict-{label}` and tooltip carrying the verdictReason threshold string. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
