    body: 'Iter 195. PIVOT FROM PRIMARY: original iter 195 plan from iter 194 verify-fire was to pull 24h rolling-average emission share from Taostats `/api/subnet/history/v1` per held netuid for a sustained signal — would let chip render BOTH instantaneous AND 24h-mean and let EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT classify on the aggregate. RESEARCH PROBE (3 endpoints, ~12 curls): (a) `/api/subnet/history/v1?netuid=75&limit=30&order=block_number_desc` returns 30 daily snapshots for Hippius (timestamps 23:59:48Z each day, blocks ~7200 apart = 24h, total_items 464 going back to subnet registration); but `emission` field is "0" on every single row, AND on `/api/subnet/latest/v1?netuid=75` right now, AND on Hippius rows across the past 30 days — so the field is a per-instant snapshot of THIS BLOCK\'s emission, not a 24h aggregate. (b) Verified across 4 known-active subnets (Targon sn4, Taoshi sn8, Vision sn19, sn64) — all show `emission=0` across 7-day windows of daily snapshots. This is the same Yuma rotation that iter 194 documented: at any instant only ~38/128 subnets show non-zero emission, and the snapshot at 23:59:48Z UTC catches whichever subnets happened to be in the rotation\'s OFF position. The "daily snapshot at midnight" is just 1 sample of 20 epochs per day — not an aggregate. (c) Probed `/api/dtao/subnet/latest/v1` and `/api/dtao/emission/latest/v1` for a dtao-specific aggregate — both empty (endpoints don\'t exist). (d) `/api/subnet/distribution/v1` empty. CONCLUSION: no Taostats free-or-paid endpoint surfaces a 24h-mean emission share. To get sustained signal we\'d need to either self-sample `/api/subnet/latest/v1?netuid=N` every Yuma tempo (~12 calls/h × 128 subnets = 1536 API calls/h, well above Standard plan budget; cron-store-aggregate in Vercel KV is viable for a future iter) or read EmissionValues storage directly from the Substrate chain via free-RPC (the iter 164/165/167 freeRpc.js stack already supports state_call patterns — but the EmissionValues vec is per-block, same snapshot problem). PIVOT to ALT (c) symmetric §3 emission chip — smallest meaningful slice that completes the iter 193 surface-symmetry pattern without claiming new data we don\'t have. SHIP (2-file): (A) lib/report.js — yieldSection() perPosition mapping at line ~1869 adds emissionPct read via new subnetEmissionPct(nid) helper (matches the existing subnetPrice(nid) pattern at line ~1867, both read from screener?.byNetuid?.[nid]); helper at line ~1869 with Number.isFinite guard for null/NaN; iter 195 comment block above the helper cites §1 portfolio() for the SNAPSHOT caveat so future readers see the linkage. (B) app/_components/Report.jsx — §3 yield-table subnet column at line ~1743 adopts the iter 193 chip render verbatim (same null-guard, same three-tier classifier, same tier-label phrases, same tooltip copy, same `(epoch)` glyph suffix from iter 194). No new CSS — reuses the .subnet-emit-chip + .emit-high + .emit-fair + .emit-off-epoch rules from iter 193+194. WHY VERBATIM COPY: the iter 193 chip is the canonical surface for emission_pct; §3 should teach the same per-epoch semantics with the same words so a user scanning both surfaces doesn\'t learn two slightly-different vocabularies for the same signal. SMOKE TARGET (after deploy): live coldkey URL (Jai\'s Subnets `/report/5EKFph3D839fxdbQwhAHyM4CQzBHNpLSecUAteNZKqW1G5cd` per iter 194 verify lesson — direct /report/<ss58> route, not the entry-page-hop /?coldkey= URL) §3 yield table should now show `· 0.00% emit (epoch)` chip in the Subnet column next to "sn{N} {name}", mirroring §1 chip exactly. NON-CHANGES THIS ITER: lib/ai-insights.js unchanged (§0 prompt already reads emissionPct via existing channels); lib/bittensor-kb.js unchanged (KB doesn\'t need a new section for a symmetric render); app/globals.css unchanged (reuses iter 193+194 CSS rules); EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT logic unchanged; CSV unchanged (buildYieldCsv at Report.jsx doesn\'t currently emit emissionPct — could be added in a future iter if useful for CSV consumers, but not load-bearing). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
