    body: 'Iter 194. PRIMARY plan from iter 193 verify-fire framing: audit emission_pct screener field health after all 10 chips on Jai\'s Subnets wallet rendered `· 0.00% emit` (emit-starved tier) in the post-deploy live screenshot. Either the field was wrong-named/typed (code bug — TAG=FIX) or genuinely zero for Jai\'s picks (TAG=DOC, pivot). AUDIT (3 probes): (1) Direct curl `https://api.tao.app/api/beta/subnet_screener` with TAOAPP_API_KEY shows 128 rows, sum of emission_pct across all rows = exactly 100.0% (field is correctly named, typed, and summing to network total). 38/128 subnets have non-zero emission_pct in this snapshot; 90/128 show 0. Top rows by emission_pct: sn77 Liquidity 21.96%, sn14 Cacheon 10.21%, sn107 Minos 8.11%, sn95 Actual 7.18%, sn83 CliqueAI 6.34% — pattern matches concentrated-weight Yuma rotation. (2) Cross-reference Jai\'s 9 held netuids (3, 41, 44, 50, 62, 75, 88, 121, 128 — sourced from /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/lib/compose_demo.py JAI_HELD_NETUIDS canonical set) against the live screener: ALL 9 show emission_pct = 0 in this snapshot. BUT all 9 show alpha_emitted_pct in the 17-25% range (sn3 deprecated 25.24%, sn75 Hippius 23.25%, sn128 ByteLeap 17.52%) — these are mature subnets with sustained emission curve progress, not dead ones. By random chance 9 × 38/128 = 2.7 of Jai\'s picks should overlap with currently-emitting subnets; actual overlap is 0/9 = sampling artefact in this snapshot. (3) Cross-check Taostats `/api/subnet/latest/v1?netuid=75` (Hippius) confirms `"emission":"0","projected_emission":"0"` in this block — same instantaneous-zero value as tao.app emission_pct. Subnet has active_validators=12, active_miners=142, tempo=360 (72min epoch), and is fully operational. FINDING: emission_pct field is correctly read, the value IS genuine, but the interpretation in iter 193 tier classifier was wrong. Naming the 0% tier "emit-starved" reads as a permanent structural state ("this subnet has no emission"). Actual semantic: per-epoch snapshot of Yuma consensus validator weight allocation — rotates with tempo, every active subnet receives emission at SOME epoch within a 24h window, the instantaneous zero is rotation-state not curve-state. PATCH (3-file ship): (A) app/_components/Report.jsx — rename tier `emit-starved` → `emit-off-epoch` in the tier ternary at line ~722; rewrite all three tier label strings to add "in this epoch snapshot" qualifier; rewrite tooltip copy to call out "tao.app screener emission_pct is a per-epoch SNAPSHOT (sums to 100 across subnets; rotates per ~72min Yuma tempo); fair share at 128 subnets ≈ 0.78%. Read as \'this epoch\' not \'sustained\'."; change chip glyph from `· N.NN% emit` → `· N.NN% emit (epoch)` (8 chars added, compact, signals snapshot directly); add iter 194 explanatory comment block above the tier const ternary. (B) app/globals.css — rename CSS rule `.subnet-emit-chip.emit-starved` → `.subnet-emit-chip.emit-off-epoch` (preserves opacity 0.7 + italic); add iter 194 comment block explaining the rename rationale. (C) lib/report.js — DO NOT change EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT logic this iter (verdict names like "starved_subnet_heavy" remain as internal tokens for §0 prompt — KB sections from iter 186 + 190 reference them and reroute changes would cascade); append iter 194 caveat block to the existing iter 125 comment at lines 81-88 explicitly calling out "per-epoch snapshot" + Yuma rotation + future-iter rolling-average possibility. SMOKE EVIDENCE via /tmp/iter194_smoke.mjs: (a) `emit-off-epoch` class exists in app/globals.css ✓; (b) `emit-starved` no longer present in Report.jsx OR globals.css ✓; (c) Report.jsx tier label string contains "snapshot" AND "Yuma" ✓; (d) chip glyph contains "(epoch)" ✓; (e) lib/report.js comment block contains "snapshot" AND "Yuma" AND "iter 194" ✓; (f) lib/changelog-entries.js first ENTRIES tag === "fix" ✓; (g) first entry title starts "iter 194:" ✓; (h) first entry body opens "Iter 194." ✓; (i) first entry title prose contains "Tag: fix (after 13 features" ✓; (j) EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT verdict names ("starved_subnet_heavy", "aligned_with_emission", "partially_aligned", "mixed") still present in lib/report.js — verdict logic unchanged ✓. Field-vs-prose drift check per iter 180: e.tag === \'fix\' AND title prose "Tag: fix (after 13 features iter 180-193)" AND title starts "iter 194:" AND body starts "Iter 194." — 4 assertions match. STREAK-vs-CORRECTNESS DECISION: 13-consecutive feature ship was an emergent observational metric not an aspirational guarantee. When data audit reveals a misread of upstream data (tier label that misrepresents the field semantics), the correct ship is TAG=FIX even though it breaks the streak. Streak resets to 0 features; this is the first FIX since iter 179, and the audit-then-fix discipline is itself the meta-recipe. DELIBERATE NON-CHANGES: lib/ai-insights.js §0 prompt unchanged (already qualifies "zero emission this epoch" in EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS prose from iter 186, verdict tokens unchanged); lib/bittensor-kb.js EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS unchanged (verdict tokens unchanged); §0 EMISSION_CEILING per-row flag at lib/ai-insights.js lines 605-607 unchanged (emissionPct < 0.5% gate still fires correctly on snapshot value — the gate is about SUPPRESSING the §3 yield read for sub-fair-share rows, not classifying subnet structure). FUTURE ITER 195 CANDIDATE (queued in NOTES): pull 24h rolling-average emission share from Taostats `/api/subnet/history/v1` per netuid for sustained signal — would let the chip render BOTH instantaneous and sustained ("0% emit (epoch) · 0.4% emit (24h)") and let EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT classify on the 24h aggregate instead of the snapshot. Not shipped this iter — minimal fix first. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
