    body: 'Iter 193. Second slice on priority #3 (more detailed report) after iter 192 first slice surfaced subnet-field shape (median APY + N validators) across §0 prompt rows and §3 yield-table. Same "data already computed, never rendered" pattern: lib/report.js portfolio() has been computing emissionPct on every position row since iter 125 (typed via the tao.app screener emission_pct field, which sums to 100 across all 128 subnets so each subnet\'s fair share is ≈ 0.78%). §0 EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_VERDICT (iter 186) already consumed it for the portfolio-weighted aligned/partial/starved verdict — but the user-facing §1 top-10 table still showed only subnet name with no structural ceiling context. A user reading the top-10 saw sn{N} as a name + size + 24h/7d move, with no signal whether that subnet is capturing network emission ("high-emission, above 1.0% fair share") or starved ("zero emission this epoch — validator weights routed elsewhere"). That structural context is the single biggest gap between "%-of-portfolio" and "is this position structurally sustainable" — addressed inline now as a quiet `· N.NN% emit` chip beside the SubnetLink. Three-tier opacity (emit-high ≥1.0% at 0.95 + 500-weight, emit-fair at 0.85, emit-starved ==0 at 0.7 italic) intentionally avoids green/red — the §0 EMISSION_ALIGNMENT narrative owns the verdict, the chip is anchoring context. Tooltip teaches the math (network emission_pct sums to 100 across all subnets; fair share at 128 subnets ≈ 0.78%; ≥1.0% materially above fair share). 13th consecutive feature ship (180+181+182+183+184+185+186+187+188+189+190+192+193; iter 191 META skipped per meta-iter edge case). Field-vs-prose drift check (iter 180) holds: e.tag === \'feature\', title prose `Tag: feature (13th consecutive...)`, title starts `iter 193:`, body starts `Iter 193.` — all 4 assertions match. Additive only — no §0 prompt change, no §3 render change beyond the inline chip, no schema change. CSV unchanged (buildPortfolioCsv at Report.jsx line 105 already emits emissionPct).',
