    body: 'Iter 192. First slice on priority #3 (more detailed report) after the iter 180-190 priority #2 verdict-label coverage sweep (8 ships, 11 consecutive features) wrapped on iter 190 and iter 191 META memorialised the recipe in three lesson memo drafts (/tmp/iter191-lessons/). Sweep is over; pivot to deepening the deterministic report surfaces with already-computed data that was never rendered. yieldSection in lib/report.js has been computing subnetMedianApy + subnetValidatorCount on every perPosition row since the validator-yield refactor (subnetSummary map at line 1841, projected onto each row at lines 1885-1886), but the only downstream consumer was buildYieldCsv (line 194) — the §0 AI prompt and the §3 user-facing yield-table both showed only Subnet best, leaving Δ to best as a gap against an absolute target rather than an outlier-vs-par check against a typed field. The same 6pp gap to best reads as a real lift on a 2-validator subnet (median ≈ best) but as a non-sustainable outlier on a 40-validator subnet where the user is sitting 1pp above median — without the field shape, neither the model nor the user can tell which. Three surfaces deepen: (1) lib/ai-insights.js §0 yield block Re-delegation opportunities — each top-5-by-lift row now appends `[subnet field: median X% across N validators]` after current/best APY framing, plus a closing read-rule paragraph teaching the model to read best in context of field shape (thin field with median ≈ best = real lift; wide field with median below you = best is tail-epoch outlier, lift may not sustain through re-delegation cycle); (2) lib/ai-insights.js §0 Per-position yield quartet block — each top-5-by-TAO-value row Plan APY (7d) line appends `· field median X% across N val` after the lift/stray/direction notes, before the verdict label, so the model reads the row position in the field alongside the quartet direction and stray flags; (3) app/_components/Report.jsx §3 yield-table Subnet best cell — adds a quiet subtitle line `median X% · N val` under the best APY value, with a tooltip on .subnet-field span codifying the read-rule (thin field gap = real lift, wide field with median below you = outlier-best, gap may not sustain). New .subnet-field / .field-lbl / .field-val CSS in globals.css (var(--dim) text, font-size 11px, tabular-nums, line-height 1.3) matches the existing .apy-fallback quietness — anchoring context for the Δ-to-best column, not actionable in itself. Zero new data flow (subnetSummary already computed once per netuid in yieldSection; rendered three times). Field-vs-prose drift check per iter 180 lesson: e.tag === \'feature\', title prose `Tag: feature (12th consecutive...)`, title starts `iter 192:`, body starts `Iter 192.` — all 4 assertions match. Non-blocking: KB layer-stack unchanged; PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff (updated_at 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z, ~20 days). Natural iter 193 candidates: (a) priority #3 second slice — historical staking flows summary (7d/30d net-flow rollup, parallel to existing single-snapshot staking flow); (b) drawdown stats expansion — durations percentiles per iter 121 followup; (c) per-subnet emission share visual chip in §1 portfolio top-10; (d) priority #1 free-API PnL continued audit (Substrate RPC / SubVortex / Subnet 19 ChainAPI candidates from iter 47 redirect).',
