    body:
      'Iter 183. PRIMARY plan was PATH C from iter 182 (priority #2 first slice — build lib/bittensor-kb.md from scratch). On re-clone the discovery: priority #2 has been BUILT FOR MONTHS. lib/bittensor-kb.js exists and ships 13 KB sections (TERMINOLOGY, YIELD_BANDS, FLAG_HEURISTICS, RECOMMENDATION_HEURISTICS, SUBNET_MATURITY, TIME_WINDOW_HEURISTICS, VALIDATOR_HEURISTICS, VALIDATOR_YIELD_BREAKDOWN_HEURISTICS, CATEGORY_HEURISTICS, PNL_DECOMPOSITION, DRAWDOWN_HEURISTICS, STAKING_FLOW_HEURISTICS, EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS), 33 dossiered subnets in SUBNET_DOSSIER, 10 category groupings in SUBNET_CATEGORIES + CATEGORY_INFO, and helper functions categoriseSubnet / portfolioCategoryBreakdown / dossierForPositions. KB_TEXT is appended to SYSTEM_PROMPT at lib/ai-insights.js line 59. Per-position dossier + category breakdown are also injected into the user prompt. The iter-47 redirect priority #2 ("AI knowledge base inside the app") is operationally LANDED, not pending. The user prompt\'s framing of PRIMARY=PATH C was stale. Re-running it would create a duplicate file and overwrite real work. PIVOT: instead of duplicating, find the actual gap. Reading lib/ai-insights.js + lib/bittensor-kb.js + lib/report.js, the gap is downstream: §0 hands the model multi-window verdict labels from iter 137 multiWindowDurabilityVerdict() (9 labels: dormant_harvest_only, flat, one_off_spike, fading_flow, recent_reversal_to_accumulation, recent_reversal_to_distribution, sustained_accumulation, sustained_distribution, mixed) and the iter 140 multi-window price-momentum block (6 labels: flat, sustained_uptrend, sustained_downtrend, recent_reversal_to_up, recent_reversal_to_down, chop). But there is no KB section codifying how to READ these labels — gpt-oss-20b receives the labels in the user prompt and either re-paraphrases the verdictReason inline or drops them entirely. PATCH: add MULTI_WINDOW_DURABILITY_HEURISTICS export const to lib/bittensor-kb.js (3.97KB section) with one explicit read-rule per label plus a cross-window reading rule. KEY RULES: dormant_harvest_only → wallet IS the strategy, do NOT recommend behavioural rebalancing; sustained_distribution → frame harvesting not alarm, do NOT add consider-trimming rec because they\'re already trimming; recent_reversal_to_accumulation → name reversal explicitly, do not extrapolate to "accumulation resumed" until 90d confirms; one_off_spike → narrate the event but do not extrapolate into a regime change; flat → suppress the flow read entirely; mwpm sustained_downtrend → do NOT trim on 1d move when 30d is the bigger story, the position is already in drawdown regime, sizing/concentration is the lever not yield-chasing; mwpm recent_reversal_to_up/down → name reversal, do not extrapolate, "dead-cat-bounce" vocabulary for a 1d/7d reversal inside a 30d sustained_downtrend; mwpm chop → suppress momentum framing in Recs. CROSS-WINDOW READING RULE: treats durability × momentum × single-window staking-flow as three orthogonal axes with explicit AGREE / DISAGREE / SHORT-vs-LONG guidance — when durability and momentum AGREE (e.g. sustained_distribution + sustained_downtrend) narrate as one story; when they DISAGREE (sustained_accumulation + sustained_downtrend) the user is fighting the tape and flag it; when single-window flow CONTRADICTS multi-window durability, name the contrast not pick one window. KB_TEXT template gains the new section by appending ${MULTI_WINDOW_DURABILITY_HEURISTICS} after EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS. SMOKE EVIDENCE (direct node --input-type=module import): 12/12 checks PASS. MULTI_WINDOW export non-empty ✓; present in KB_TEXT ✓; mwDur labels dormant_harvest_only / sustained_distribution / recent_reversal_to_accumulation / one_off_spike / fading_flow all present in final KB_TEXT ✓; mwpm labels sustained_uptrend / recent_reversal_to_down / chop all present ✓; cross-window "three orthogonal axes" rule present ✓; existing KB preamble "You have access to the following Bittensor reference" still present (no regression on existing 13 sections) ✓. KB_TEXT now 29,511 chars total (~29.5KB), the new section is 3,971 chars (~4KB). DELIBERATE NON-CHANGES: lib/ai-insights.js unchanged — the KB_TEXT interpolation in SYSTEM_PROMPT at line 59 picks up the new section automatically because KB_TEXT itself grew; no per-prompt branching needed. lib/report.js unchanged — the verdict labels already flow through portfolio.multiWindowNetFlow / stakingFlowVerdict.multiWindowDurability / pnl.multiWindowPriceMomentum, and the read-rule is what was missing not the data plumbing. SUBNET_DOSSIER, SUBNET_CATEGORIES, CATEGORY_INFO unchanged — adding more dossier entries would require authoritative source verification that doesn\'t fit one fire, and would risk shipping wrong subnet purposes to production. All 13 existing KB sections unchanged — additive only. DIFF SUMMARY: lib/bittensor-kb.js +47/-0 (one new export const block + ${MULTI_WINDOW_DURABILITY_HEURISTICS} interpolation appended to KB_TEXT template), lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry). Bundle delta: ~4KB on the bundled KB_TEXT string at runtime; no new deps. Pre-commit: `node --check lib/bittensor-kb.js` PASSED, `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. Tag: feature (4th consecutive after iter 180/181/182 — priority #1 graduation arc is end-to-end DONE in production; iter 183 is the first priority #2 DEEPENING since the pivot). Pre-push field-vs-prose drift check (per iter 180 lesson): read ENTRIES[0] after writing, structured `e.tag === "feature"` AND title prose says "Tag: feature (4th consecutive)" → MATCHES, no drift. EXPECTED POST-DEPLOY VERIFY: changelog top H2 starts verbatim "iter 183: priority #2 deepening — lib/bittensor-kb.js gains MULTI_WINDOW_DURABILITY_HEURISTICS", tag badge renders "feature" (4th consecutive after iter 180/181/182). Live durability proof requires a wallet whose multi-window verdicts compute non-trivially (e.g. mum_subnets with year-long flow, or any wallet where mwDur fires sustained_accumulation/distribution) — on that wallet, the next /api/insights run should reflect the new read-rule in the Summary / What Changed framing (e.g. "year-long sustained_distribution — harvesting posture" instead of generic "negative flow"). ITER 184 CANDIDATES: (A) propose lessons_taostats_endpoint_flap_multilayer.md + lessons_changelog_field_vs_prose_drift.md to Jai as durable lesson memos — priority #1 arc has shipped end-to-end across 4 surfaces, pattern is ripe to memorialise (could include now also the "verify-actual-state-before-pivoting" lesson from iter 183\'s PATH-C-already-done discovery); (B) more priority #2 deepening — audit which other §0 verdict labels lack KB read-rules (e.g. drawdown labels at_peak/resilient_absorb/recovered/beyond_historical_tail/flag_worthy/within_typical_stretch/recent_deep_dip/shallow_but_extended/recent_noise/material_dip already have DRAWDOWN_HEURISTICS but the validator-concentration labels single_validator/extreme_concentration/concentrated/moderate/diversified may have a similar coverage gap to audit); (C) priority #3 first slice — "more detailed report": candidates include longer time windows, drawdown stats expansion, what-changed-between-snapshots diff; (D) extend graduation gate to broader Taostats endpoint flap (not just /delegation); (E) trace mantat\'s still-unknown 500-throwing endpoint via Vercel runtime logs. PRIMARY for iter 184: pick (B) — keep the priority #2 deepening cadence going, audit remaining verdict-label coverage gaps before pivoting to priority #3. ALT: (A) close the documentation loop now that the pattern has shipped. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
