    body:
      'Iter 182. Path A from iter 181 plan: extend the priority #1 graduation arc into the subscription email digest. This is the FOURTH and final surface — the arc now spans backend gate → on-page UI footnote → AI write-up prompt → subscription email — and a wallet hitting a Taostats /delegation flap mid-snapshot will see its free-API source disclosed across every place that renders the portfolio total. SAME CONDITIONAL GATE everywhere by construction: `portfolio.canonicalSource === "free-api-fallback" && typeof portfolio.canonicalTao === "number"`. Single source of truth for the gate is set in lib/report.js iter 180 (`portClean.canonicalSource = "free-api-fallback"` when `pnl.partial===true && shadowFreeApi.ok===true`). Three downstream consumers (UI footnote app/_components/Report.jsx, AI prompt lib/ai-insights.js, email digest lib/report-email.js) all read the same fields off `report.portfolio`. PATCH (lib/report-email.js +24/-2): added two const blocks. canonicalBlock (HTML, ~14 lines): rendered after aiBlock and before the PnL h2, gold-bordered dark card with the disclosure copy and reason in a monospace `<code>` chip — matches the visual language of the rest of the email (same #f9a826 accent, same #131720 background). canonicalTextBlock (plain-text, 3 lines): rendered before aiTextBlock in the text array, single-line note with no HTML. Both gated on the SAME conditional (canonicalSource === "free-api-fallback" AND typeof canonicalTao === "number"), so html + text stay in lockstep with the rest of the surfaces. DELIBERATE NON-CHANGES: lib/report.js + app/_components/Report.jsx + lib/ai-insights.js all unchanged this iter — they were the upstream three surfaces shipped in iter 180 + 181. PnL section (gt block) and Top 5 + movers blocks unchanged — the canonical disclosure is about portfolio.canonicalTao (not gt.currentPortfolioTao which is a separate ground-truth lineage from the snapshot history). app/api/cron/weekly-emails route unchanged — it just calls renderEmail; the conditional is inside renderEmail. Subscription email body shape unchanged for ALL non-graduated snapshots (the canonical blocks render as empty strings) — zero regression risk on happy-path digests. SMOKE EVIDENCE (/tmp/iter182_smoke.mjs): direct import of renderEmail (no temp export needed; already an exported function). Exercise 4 cases against the rendered { html, text } pair. Case A (no canonicalSource): NEITHER html nor text contains "Free-API source" / "free-API substrate-RPC fallback" ✓. Case B (canonicalSource=free-api-fallback, canonicalTao=3.1295886833, canonicalReason=delegation_rate_limited): html contains "Free-API source" + "3.1296 τ" + "delegation_rate_limited" + "Treat as authoritative" ✓; text contains "free-API substrate-RPC fallback" + "3.1296" + "delegation_rate_limited" ✓. Case C (canonicalSource set but canonicalReason undefined): both html and text fall back to "delegation_rate_limited" via the `|| "delegation_rate_limited"` default ✓. Case D (canonicalSource set but canonicalTao undefined): the typeof guard correctly refuses to graduate — NEITHER html NOR text contains the disclosure block ✓. All 4 PASS at runtime. PRE-COMMIT: `node --check lib/report-email.js` PASSED. Tag: feature (3rd consecutive after iter 180 backend+UI + iter 181 AI prompt — the user-visible graduation arc is now complete end-to-end). Pre-push field-vs-prose drift check (per iter 180 lesson): read ENTRIES[0] after writing, confirmed `e.tag === "feature"` AND title prose says "Tag: feature (3rd consecutive)" → MATCHES, no drift. EXPECTED POST-DEPLOY VERIFY: changelog top H2 starts verbatim "iter 182: complete priority #1 graduation arc end-to-end into subscription email digest", tag badge renders "feature" (3rd consecutive), no UI regression on §1 Total (iter 180 footnote still works), email-preview endpoint still 200s. Live durability: when mum_subnets (or any wallet hitting Taostats /delegation 429 mid-snapshot) generates its next Monday digest, the rendered email should contain the canonical block + text. ITER 183 CANDIDATES: (A) propose lessons_taostats_endpoint_flap_multilayer.md + lessons_changelog_field_vs_prose_drift.md to Jai as durable lesson memos — graduation arc has now shipped end-to-end (backend gate iter 180 → on-page UI footnote iter 180 → AI write-up prompt iter 181 → subscription email digest iter 182), pattern is RIPE to memorialise; (B) extend graduation gate to ALSO fire when /api/account/latest flaps (currently gate is /delegation-specific — broader Taostats endpoint flap should also graduate to shadow, but requires audit of which Taostats endpoints shadowFreeApi can actually replace); (C) priority #2 first slice — start building the Bittensor domain KB (lib/bittensor-kb.md): subnet purposes, what\'s normal/abnormal terminology, recommendation heuristics — wire into lib/ai-insights.js system prompt so the AI write-up has real domain ground; (D) trace mantat\'s still-unknown 500-throwing endpoint via Vercel runtime logs (iter 178 surfaced as the last opaque failure mode). PRIMARY: pick (C) — priority #1 arc is end-to-end DONE, time to pivot to priority #2 per Jai\'s iter-47 redirect. ALT: (A) close the documentation loop first. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
