    body:
      'Iter 181. Path A from iter 180 plan: wire canonicalTao / canonicalSource / canonicalReason into the AI insights system + user prompts so the AI write-up reflects the graduated source during Taostats /delegation flaps. ROOT GAP: iter 180 graduated the §1 portfolio surface (backend portClean decoration + UI footnote rendering), but the AI write-up at /api/insights consumes report.portfolio via lib/ai-insights.js buildUserPrompt() which only read p.totalTao — so even when iter 180\'s graduation engaged in the UI, the AI write-up would still describe "portfolio total: 5.5τ" without disclosing that 5.5 came from shadowFreeApi (not Taostats canonical). PATCH (lib/ai-insights.js +8/-0): immediately after the existing `Total: ${p.totalTao.toFixed(3)}τ ...` line and before the `lines.push("")` separator, insert a conditional block: `if (p.canonicalSource === "free-api-fallback" && typeof p.canonicalTao === "number") { const reason = p.canonicalReason || "delegation_rate_limited"; lines.push("NOTE: The portfolio total of " + p.canonicalTao.toFixed(4) + "τ is sourced from free-API substrate RPC because Taostats canonical /delegation was rate-limited (reason: " + reason + ") at snapshot time. Treat this as authoritative for this snapshot."); }`. Why directly after Total: gives the AI the canonical number first (as the existing prompt structure does), then immediately discloses provenance — the AI cannot misframe it as Taostats canonical because the next line in the user prompt says explicitly free-API. Why p.canonicalTao.toFixed(4) (not totalTao): canonicalTao IS the graduated number; totalTao remains unchanged per iter 180 (computed from holdings × screener prices). 4dp matches iter 180 UI footnote convention. Why `Treat this as authoritative`: tells the model NOT to caveat further — the graduation gate already decided this number is valid; the model doesn\'t need to add "this might be off" hedging. Same conditional gate as iter 180 UI (canonicalSource === "free-api-fallback" AND typeof canonicalTao === "number") so prompt and UI stay in lockstep — if iter 182+ changes the gate, both surfaces have to update together (single source of truth: report.portfolio.canonicalSource). SMOKE EVIDENCE (/tmp/iter181_smoke_runtime.mjs): temporarily export buildUserPrompt by copying lib/ai-insights.js → lib/ai-insights-test.mjs and sed-replacing `function buildUserPrompt` → `export function buildUserPrompt` (test-only, deleted after smoke), then import and exercise 3 cases. Case A (no canonicalSource): prompt does NOT contain "free-API substrate RPC" ✓. Case B (canonicalSource=free-api-fallback, canonicalTao=3.1295886833, canonicalReason=delegation_rate_limited): prompt contains "3.1296τ" (toFixed(4) of 3.1295886833 rounds up), "free-API substrate RPC", "delegation_rate_limited", "Treat this as authoritative" ✓. Case C (canonicalSource set but canonicalReason undefined): prompt still contains "delegation_rate_limited" because of the `|| "delegation_rate_limited"` default ✓. All 3 PASS at runtime. DELIBERATE NON-CHANGES: SYSTEM_PROMPT unchanged — the analyst persona, four-section rule, plain-speaking voice are unaffected; only the user prompt gains a conditional note. buildVerdictFallback unchanged — fallback verdict path is for COMPLETE upstream failure, not for partial graduation. peekCachedInsights / validateSections / patchMissingSections all unchanged. lib/report.js + app/_components/Report.jsx unchanged — iter 180\'s decoration + UI footnote are the upstream source of truth; iter 181 is a downstream consumer. lib/report-email.js NOT touched this iter — subscription email graduation is deferred to iter 182 (Path B from iter 180) to keep iter 181 small + shippable. DIFF SUMMARY: lib/ai-insights.js +8/-0 (conditional note block under Portfolio Total), lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry). Bundle delta: ~0.6KB lib/ai-insights.js, no new deps. Pre-commit: `node --check lib/ai-insights.js` PASSED, `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. Tag: feature (2nd consecutive after iter 180 — extending the user-visible graduation arc; tag field MATCHES prose claim per the field-vs-prose drift bug iter 180 hit, now part of the iter-181 verify protocol). EXPECTED POST-DEPLOY VERIFY: changelog top H2 starts verbatim "iter 181: extend priority #1 graduation arc into AI write-up", tag badge renders "feature" (2nd consecutive), no UI regression on §1 Total (iter 180 footnote still works). When mum_subnets (or any wallet hitting Taostats /delegation 429 mid-snapshot) re-runs /api/insights, the AI write-up should reference "free-API substrate RPC" + the graduated TAO total in its first ## Portfolio section paragraph. ITER 182 CANDIDATES: (A) extend graduation to subscription email lib/report-email.js (Monday digest also discloses free-API source on flap snapshots — same conditional block, render as inline HTML/text note); (B) propose lessons_taostats_endpoint_flap_multilayer.md + lessons_changelog_field_vs_prose_drift.md to Jai as durable lesson memos (the graduation arc has now shipped end-to-end across backend + UI + AI prompt; the pattern is ready to memorialise); (C) trace mantat\'s still-unknown 500-throwing endpoint via Vercel runtime logs (iter 178 surfaced as the last opaque failure mode); (D) extend graduation gate to additionally fire when /api/account/latest itself flaps (currently gate is delegation-specific — broader Taostats endpoint flap should also graduate to shadow, but requires careful audit of which Taostats endpoints shadowFreeApi can actually replace). Pick A or B first — A continues the user-facing arc; B closes the documentation loop. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
