    title: 'iter 180: priority #1 GRADUATION MILESTONE — shadowFreeApi (free substrate-RPC) graduates to canonical portfolio source when iter 179\'s pnl.partial flag fires. When p.partial===true (Taostats /api/delegation/v1 rate-limited per iter 179 wrap) AND gt.shadowFreeApi.ok===true, decorate §1 portfolio with canonicalSource:"free-api-fallback" + canonicalTao = shadowFreeApi.totalTao + canonicalReason carried from p.partialReason. UI patch app/_components/Report.jsx renders an inline footnote under §1 Total: "ℹ️ free-API source (X.XXXX τ via substrate RPC) — Taostats canonical /delegation rate-limited this snapshot" so users see the graduated number with explicit provenance. This is the first time the report makes a binding decision to surface free-API data as the canonical figure during a Taostats flap, rather than just degrading or partial-flagging. /tmp/iter180_smoke.mjs proved all 4 gate combinations: A happy-path (no graduation, no decoration) ✓ B graduation engages with correct canonicalTao + canonicalSource + canonicalReason ✓ C p.partial=true but shadow failed → NO graduation (correct, no shadow to graduate to) ✓ D shadow ok but p not partial → NO graduation (correct, no flap to graduate around) ✓. Backend lib/report.js +18/-0, UI app/_components/Report.jsx +20/-1; bundle delta ~1.5KB, no new deps. Tag: feature (not research) — this is a user-visible architectural milestone, the priority #1 graduation Jai redirected the build toward at iter 47. Iter 181 candidates: surface canonicalTao in subscription email/ai-insights prompt; wrap mantat\'s still-unknown 500-throwing endpoint.',
    body:
      'Iter 180. PRIORITY #1 GRADUATION MILESTONE landed. Jai\'s iter-47 redirect ranked "free-API PnL — same ground-truth from a FREE source" as priority #1; iter 177 (CoinGecko /price fallback) + iter 178 (sweep surfacing /api/delegation/v1 429 as remaining bottleneck) + iter 179 (defensive try/catch decorating pnl.partial=true) built the gates. Iter 180 finally graduates shadowFreeApi.totalTao (computed off the free substrate RPC chain probe — independent of Taostats heavy endpoints) to canonicalSource:"free-api-fallback" on §1 portfolio when the Taostats path is degraded. ROOT CONCEPT: portfolio.totalTao itself ships unchanged (computed from holdings × screener alpha prices, which doesn\'t fail when /delegation flaps); the new canonicalTao + canonicalSource fields announce "here\'s the parallel free-API number that we\'re prepared to surface as the canonical figure when Taostats is down." UI renders a small footnote under §1 Total so users see provenance. BACKEND PATCH (lib/report.js +18/-0, after `const { allPositions, ...portClean } = port;` block circa line 2604): `if (p?.partial === true && gt?.shadowFreeApi?.ok === true) { portClean.canonicalSource = "free-api-fallback"; portClean.canonicalTao = gt.shadowFreeApi.totalTao; portClean.canonicalReason = p.partialReason || "delegation_rate_limited"; }`. Why p.partial (not gt.partial): iter 179 set the flag on p (§3) because pnl() consumes history; the gate reads the same flag. Why gt.shadowFreeApi.ok: confirms the shadow path actually produced a number we can stand behind — without that confirmation, surfacing "free-api-fallback" with no number would be a regression. UI PATCH (app/_components/Report.jsx +20/-1, immediately after §1 Total/USD/AUD/Positions stat row): conditional render block `{p.canonicalSource === "free-api-fallback" && Number.isFinite(p.canonicalTao) && (<p className="canonical-footnote" title="..." style={{fontSize:"0.85em",color:"var(--muted,#8a93a3)",marginTop:"6px"}}>ℹ️ free-API source (X.XXXX τ via substrate RPC) — Taostats canonical /delegation rate-limited this snapshot</p>)}`. Inline styles (no globals.css change this iter — additive only, keeps diff small for iter 180; if Jai wants polish a follow-up iter can move to .css). Title attribute gives the full explanation on hover. Reason-aware copy: when canonicalReason==="delegation_rate_limited" the footnote says "/delegation rate-limited"; otherwise generic "degraded". SMOKE (/tmp/iter180_smoke.mjs run from VPS): four cases simulating the EXACT iter 180 gate. Case A (p NOT partial, shadow ok) — portClean has NO canonicalSource/canonicalTao/canonicalReason ✓ (happy path, no graduation needed). Case B (p.partial=true reason="delegation_rate_limited", shadow ok totalTao=3.1295886833773974) — portClean has canonicalSource="free-api-fallback", canonicalTao=3.1295886833773974, canonicalReason="delegation_rate_limited" ✓ (the graduation milestone fires correctly). Case C (p.partial=true, shadow FAILED) — portClean has NO canonicalSource ✓ (correctly refuses to graduate to a nonexistent shadow number). Case D (shadow ok, p NOT partial) — portClean has NO canonicalSource ✓ (correctly does not preempt the canonical path when nothing is wrong). All 4 PASS. DELIBERATE NON-CHANGES: portfolio.totalTao unchanged (still computed from holdings × screener prices); pnl/pnlGroundTruth shapes unchanged (gate just READS p.partial + gt.shadowFreeApi.ok); no AI insights prompt change this iter (canonicalSource flows through report.portfolio naturally; ai-insights.js consumes data.portfolio and can read the new fields without code change — but explicit prompt wiring deferred to iter 181 so the graduation milestone itself stays small and shippable); no subscription email change this iter (same reason — report-email.js can read p.canonicalSource if Jai wants follow-up). DIFF SUMMARY: lib/report.js +18/-0 (post-portClean graduation gate block), app/_components/Report.jsx +20/-1 (footnote render under §1 Total), lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry). Bundle delta: ~1.5KB total, no new deps. Pre-commit: `node --check lib/report.js` PASSED, `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED; Report.jsx not node-checkable (JSX) — Vercel build is the validator. Tag: feature (NOT research) — this is a user-visible architectural milestone, the priority #1 graduation Jai redirected the build toward at iter 47. Breaks the 16-iter research streak deliberately. EXPECTED POST-DEPLOY VERIFY: pick a wallet whose iter 178/179 history shows /delegation flaps (mum_subnets is the canonical candidate); when Taostats /delegation 429s, response should ship http:200 with portfolio.canonicalSource="free-api-fallback" + portfolio.canonicalTao populated, and the rendered UI should show the footnote under §1 Total. When Taostats /delegation is HAPPY (most snapshots), no graduation engages and the footnote does NOT render — verifying the gate is correctly conditional and not leaking. Since iter 179 verify proved mum_subnets graduated to http:200 (no /delegation 429 during that probe), a forced-flap test may require waiting for natural Taostats flap OR re-running the iter 178/iter 176 sweep until at least one wallet trips the gate. ITER 181 PATHS: (A) wire canonicalTao into ai-insights.js system prompt so the AI write-up reflects the graduated source ("Your wallet ships X.XXXX τ via free-API — Taostats canonical is rate-limited this snapshot"); (B) extend graduation to subscription email (report-email.js); (C) wrap mantat\'s still-unknown 500-throwing endpoint (iter 178 surfaced it as unknown, Vercel runtime logs would identify); (D) propose lessons_taostats_endpoint_flap_multilayer.md now that the pattern has shipped end-to-end. Pick (A) or (C) first — (A) extends graduation into AI write-up (visible user value); (C) closes the last remaining 5xx hole. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
