    title: 'iter 179: defensive try/catch around getDelegationHistory call in buildReport — page-1 /api/delegation/v1 throws (the verbatim "Taostats /api/delegation/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." surfaced by iter 178\'s mum_subnets sweep) no longer collapse the entire report into http:500; on failure history=[] proceeds and the pnl section is decorated with partial:true, partialReason:"delegation_rate_limited", partialDetail:<verbatim Taostats error> so consumers (AI insights + §3 PnL render) can gate "realised PnL" claims behind the partial flag instead of presenting 0τ as ground truth; current_balance, emissions PnL, drawdown, volatility, taxYear, yield, recs, broader all ship unchanged via shadow + balance-history paths; endpoint-by-endpoint defensive fallback per iter 178 lesson (Taostats heavy endpoints flap independently — iter 177\'s blanket /price CoinGecko fallback couldn\'t close orthogonal /delegation throttle buckets); /tmp/iter179_smoke.mjs proved happy-path history.length=1 with no partial flag AND broken-path history=[] with p.partial=true + reason="delegation_rate_limited" verbatim; bundle delta ~0.7KB lib/report.js, no new deps; expected post-deploy: mum_subnets http:500→http:200 with pnl.partial=true (the wallet iter 178 surfaced); priority #1 graduation gate one step closer — every wallet now ships SOMETHING even when /delegation flaps',
    body:
      'Iter 179. First real code-change since iter 177. Path A from iter 178 plan: wrap the /api/delegation/v1 callsite in buildReport with defensive try/catch so a page-1 throw doesn\'t collapse the entire report. ROOT CAUSE: lib/report.js line 2364 was `const history = await getDelegationHistory(coldkey);` with no try/catch. getDelegationHistory has an iter 161 partial-data fallback for page>1 throws (return partial rows, mark `out.partial=true`), but page-1 throws bubble unchanged to preserve the iter 154 lying-catch fix. When Taostats /api/delegation/v1 throws 429 on the very first page (mum_subnets verbatim "Taostats /api/delegation/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." captured by iter 178 sweep), the throw propagated through buildReport and the entire report 500\'d — even though current_balance, emissions PnL, drawdown, volatility, taxYear, yield, recommendations, and broader were all computable from data we already had (shadow path + balance-history snapshots). PATCH: lib/report.js +24/-1. Wrap the getDelegationHistory call in try/catch. On throw, capture the error string into historyFetchError, set history=[], log a warn. Downstream pnl() iterates the empty history fine (returns spentTao=0/soldTao=0/realisedTao=0/totalPnlTao=currentTao). After the Promise.all that builds the section bag, decorate p with `{partial:true, partialReason:"delegation_rate_limited", partialDetail:<verbatim>}` so consumers can read the flag and gate any "realised PnL" claim behind it. NOT BLANKETED: only the inline buildReport call site is wrapped; getDelegationHistory itself preserves its iter 161 partial-data fallback for mid-pagination throws AND its iter 154 page-1-throw bubble. The wrap is targeted at the specific caller that has no recovery path of its own. SMOKE (/tmp/iter179_smoke.mjs run from VPS): two cases simulating the EXACT patched logic. Case A (happy path, getDelegationHistory returns [{netuid:1,action:DELEGATE,tao:1.5}]): history.length=1, fetchError=null, p.partial=undefined, p.spentTao=1.5 — verifies no regression on the happy path, partial flag does NOT engage when getDelegationHistory succeeds. Case B (broken path, getDelegationHistory throws verbatim 429): history.length=0, fetchError="Taostats /api/delegation/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later.", p.partial=true, p.partialReason="delegation_rate_limited", p.spentTao=0 — verifies catch block engages, history degrades to empty array, downstream pnl() returns zeros without throwing, decoration applies. Both PASS. DELIBERATE NON-CHANGES: lib/taostats.js getDelegationHistory unchanged (iter 161 partial-data + iter 154 page-1-throw bubble both preserved for in-helper consumers); lib/freeRpc.js + lib/freePnl.js unchanged (shadow path independent of /delegation); lib/pnlGroundTruth.js + lib/report.js pnlGroundTruth signature unchanged (the section receives no history arg — its degraded modes are already gated by rowsFetchError/balanceFetchError per iter 154/iter 159; the new partial:true is on p (§3), not gt (§2)). WHY p NOT gt: pnl()/§3 reads history; pnlGroundTruth()/§2 reads rows+balance and has its own degraded-mode machinery. The flag belongs where the data dependency is. AI INSIGHTS HOOK: lib/ai-insights.js consumes pnl + pnlGroundTruth from buildReport output; the new p.partial=true gives the prompt a clean signal to caveat any "$X realised PnL" claim with "(realised-PnL data unavailable this snapshot — Taostats /delegation rate-limited; current_balance + emissions PnL are unaffected)". No change to ai-insights.js this iter — let the field flow naturally, downstream consumers can read it. DIFF SUMMARY: lib/report.js +24/-1 (try/catch around line 2364 + post-Promise.all decoration), lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry). Bundle delta: ~0.7KB lib/report.js, no new deps. Pre-commit: `node --check lib/report.js` PASSED, `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. Tag: research (16th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168/169/170/171/172/173/174/175/176/177/178; 166 correctness interlude). EXPECTED POST-DEPLOY VERIFY: mum_subnets (iter 178 http:500 with /api/delegation/v1 429 verbatim) should land http:200 with pnl.partial=true reason="delegation_rate_limited". This is the cleanest post-deploy proof — same wallet, same upstream Taostats endpoint behavior, just a survival path the report didn\'t have before. ITER 180 PLAN: if iter 179 cleans mum_subnets, priority #1 graduation is genuinely close. Two paths: (A) graduate shadow→primary for current_balance when Taostats canonical 429s — i.e. when pnl.partial=true AND shadowFreeApi.ok=true, surface shadow as the canonical number with footnote "free-API"; (B) wrap remaining 5xx endpoints (mantat 500 unknown — need Vercel runtime logs to identify) with same try/catch + reason pattern. Pick A first (architectural milestone, not just defensive wrapping). DURABLE LESSON CANDIDATE (deferred until iter 180 evidence): "Taostats heavy endpoints flap independently; defensive fallback must be endpoint-by-endpoint (cache, free RPC, partial flag — not blanket fallback). Pattern: wrap the inline buildReport call site, capture the error string, degrade to safe empty data, decorate the affected section with partial:true + reason. Don\'t modify the helper itself if the helper has caller-agnostic invariants (e.g. iter 154 lying-catch fix)." Worth proposing to Jai after iter 180 confirms the pattern scales. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE.',
