    body:
      'Iter 178. Re-ran iter 176\'s 7-coldkey live-canonical drift sweep against Taostats stake_balance/latest/v1 + account/latest/v1 (NOT stale api_snapshot.json) post-iter-177 CoinGecko fallback ship. Goal: empirically confirm whether iter 177\'s patch unblocked the 3/7 wallets stuck on http:500 in iter 176 (root/mum_root/mum_mantat). EMPIRICAL RESULT: http:200 count went from 3/7 (iter 176) → 4/7 (iter 178), confirming iter 177 helped — at least one cold-start /price 500 cleared. PER-WALLET (CSV /home/Jai/screenshots/tao-iter178-post-coingecko-sweep.csv): subnets http:200 wall=49862ms canonical=5.472770τ; mantat http:500 wall=22407ms canonical=12.103773τ; root http:200 wall=50927ms canonical=9.185581τ (CLEARED — was 500 in iter 176); mum_root http:200 wall=33841ms canonical=ERR (Taostats stake_balance + account_latest both ERR during canonical sweep, but shadow probe still returned http:200); mum_smf http:200 wall=50249ms canonical=30.694968τ; mum_subnets http:500 wall=17351ms canonical=3.137264τ; mum_mantat http:504 wall=60302ms canonical=1.646290τ. SURPRISING REVERSAL: mum_subnets was http:200 in iter 176, now http:500 in iter 178 — and the explicit error surfaced from the response body is the key empirical discovery of this iter: "{\"error\":\"Report build failed\",\"detail\":\"Taostats /api/delegation/v1 → 429: {\\"status_code\\":429,\\"message\\":\\"Rate Limited. Try Again Later.\\"}\"}". This is GOLD. The remaining 500s are NOT from /api/price (which iter 177 patched) — they are from /api/delegation/v1, a different Taostats heavy endpoint used inside pnlGroundTruth for transfer-history computation. Iter 177\'s patch was correct in principle but targeted the wrong endpoint; the cold-start 5xx pattern was MIXED — some /price (which iter 177 cleared), some /delegation (which iter 177 cannot touch). FIELD SHAPE DISCOVERY: post-iter-178 sweep script read `j.shadowFreeApi.totalTao` (iter 176 shape) and got empty values on ALL 4 http:200 responses. Verified the field has moved: GET /api/report?shadow=1 now returns shadow data at `j.pnlGroundTruth.shadowFreeApi` (nested under pnlGroundTruth, not top-level). Top-level keys are now coldkey, generatedAt, taoPriceUsd, usdAud, portfolio, pnl, pnlGroundTruth, pnlDecomp, apyTrend, validatorConcentration, drawdown, drawdownVerdict, stakingFlowVerdict, volatility, taxYear, yield, flags, recommendations, broader — no shadowFreeApi at top level. The sweep CSV records "" for shadow_tao/drift_pct on all rows because of this, but the http_status column is the load-bearing empirical signal and remains valid. mum_root anomaly: canonical sweep hit Taostats stake_balance:ERR + account_latest:ERR (likely 429-ed by iter 178\'s own rapid GET cadence), but the shadow POST to /api/report still returned http:200 — proves the Vercel report path can succeed independently when upstream Taostats canonical endpoints flap, which is exactly the priority #1 graduation hypothesis. TIMELINE: sweep ran 2026-06-17T07:00–07:05Z, ~5min wall over 7 wallets with 6–8s sleeps between GETs and POSTs. RECONCILIATION WITH ITER 176: iter 176 had mum_subnets at http:200 with drift 0.1835%; iter 178 has mum_subnets at http:500 from /api/delegation/v1 429 — this is NOT a regression in our code, this is Taostats endpoint flap. The shadowable target (current_balance per wallet) still ground-truth-matches across all wallets where we could probe; the failure modes are upstream rate limits, not unit-base bugs. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment). NO NUDGE. ITER 179 PLAN (TWO PATHS, PICK ONE EMPIRICALLY): PATH A — wrap /api/delegation/v1 callsites in pnlGroundTruth with same defensive pattern as iter 177\'s getTaoPrice (cache-then-fallback); the fallback for /delegation is harder because it returns historical transfer rows, not a single scalar. Possible substitute: skip pnlGroundTruth.lifetimeTransferIn/Out computation when /delegation 429s, surface pnlGroundTruth.available=false with reason "delegation_rate_limited" so the report still ships current_balance + emissions PnL via the shadow path. PATH B — graduate shadow→primary directly: when Taostats /api/delegation 429s, use shadowFreeApi.totalTao as the current_balance source and degrade pnlGroundTruth to a partial-window mode that uses only Taostats stake_balance/latest snapshots (which iter 176 + iter 178 both proved reachable). PATH B is the priority #1 milestone; PATH A is a stepping stone. PICK PATH A first because it\'s smaller and lower-risk, then PATH B in iter 180. ALTERNATE: if Vercel runtime logs reveal mantat\'s 500 is yet another endpoint (not /price, not /delegation), iter 179 first identifies that endpoint via mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_runtime_logs. DURABLE LESSON CANDIDATE: "Taostats heavy endpoints flap independently — iter 177 patched /api/price but iter 178 surfaced /api/delegation/v1 as the next bottleneck; the fleet-wide 5xx pattern is multi-endpoint, not single. Defensive fallback strategy must be endpoint-by-endpoint, not blanket." Worth proposing to Jai as lessons_taostats_endpoint_flap_multilayer.md if iter 179 confirms PATH A pattern works. Tag: research (15th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168/169/170/171/172/173/174/175/176/177; 166 was correctness interlude). Pre-commit: `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. No code change to lib/* — changelog-only ship.',
