    body:
      'Iter 174. Diagnoses the alpha-share-pricing bug surfaced by iter 173\'s mum_subnets 54.89% drift. Ran /tmp/iter174_diagnose.mjs against mum_subnets coldkey 5GQAqusPNfe7qbtzXdpv6PcbgxQDG7K3nVwzmLPQKap5cw2V from VPS: called lib/freeRpc.js getColdkeyStakeAlpha() (raw runtime-API decode) + getSubnetPrices() (pool-reserves batch), cross-referenced per-(hotkey, netuid) sum against canonical positions in /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json portfolio_mum.mum_subnets. CRITICAL FINDING: the bug is NOT in the pool-price formula — those match canonical to within 2.5% (netuid 41 shadow_price 0.007810 vs canon 0.008010 = -2.50%; netuid 44 shadow 0.039539 vs canon 0.039484 = +0.14%; netuid 62 shadow 0.012790 vs canon 0.013013 = -1.72%; netuid 75 shadow 0.016721 vs canon 0.016725 = -0.02%) — within snapshot-freshness tolerance. The bug is the ALPHA AMOUNT: per-(hotkey, netuid) shadow_alpha is 11-58% OVER canonical alpha_tokens (netuid 41 Almanac shadow 31.3902 vs canon 24.1806 = +29.82%; netuid 44 Score shadow 34.0572 vs canon 30.5263 = +11.57%; netuid 62 Ridges shadow 21.0881 vs canon 13.3641 = +57.80%; netuid 75 Hippius shadow 29.8328 vs canon 26.1019 = +14.29%). ROOT CAUSE: the runtime API StakeInfoRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey returns alpha SHARES (per-coldkey fractional ownership of the hotkey\'s alpha pool), NOT alpha TOKENS. The freeRpc.js comment at line 119 + 147 calls the field "alpha-share atoms" but treats the value as alpha tokens. The pool price (SubnetTAO/SubnetAlphaIn) is TAO per alpha TOKEN, not TAO per share — so multiplying shares × price is the wrong unit base. CORRECT FORMULA: `alpha_tokens = stake_shares × TotalHotkeyAlpha(hotkey, netuid) / TotalHotkeyShares(hotkey, netuid)` then `tao_value = alpha_tokens × price`. The inflation factor `TotalHotkeyShares / TotalHotkeyAlpha` depends on per-hotkey emission accrual history, which is why drift varies wildly per (hotkey, netuid) — different validators have accumulated different share-to-token ratios. WHY ITER 167 + ITER 173 SUBNETS COLDKEY PASSED: iter 167\'s primary validation target was Mantat (dominated by netuid 0 root subnet, where shares=tokens=tao by convention, no inflation). Iter 173\'s Subnets coldkey: 58% root (3.165τ root / 5.4593τ total); non-root inflation drift was partially offset by snapshot freshness, landing at 0.10% by luck of timing. mum_subnets is the first stress test of a 100%-non-root coldkey across multiple validator hotkeys — and it exposed the bug definitively. ALSO EXPLAINS mum_smf (0.86% drift) + mum_mantat (2.75% drift): both hold ONLY netuid 0 (root). Their small drift is consistent with 24h emissions accrual since canonical snapshot (~0.027%/day root staking accrual ≈ 1% over 36 hours), NOT the alpha-shares bug. ITER 175 PATCH PLAN: (1) Add TotalHotkeyAlpha + TotalHotkeyShares storage reads to the freeRpc.js batch fetcher. Storage key layout: `xxhash128("SubtensorModule") + xxhash128("TotalHotkeyAlpha") + identity(hotkey 32B) + identity(u16 netuid LE)` for Alpha (u64 LE), same shape for TotalHotkeyShares but value is U64F64 (128-bit fixed-point, decode as u128 LE, integer part = value >> 64). (2) Per entry in getColdkeyStakeTao: `alpha_tokens = (stakeSharesAtoms × totalAlphaAtoms × 1e18) / totalSharesU64F64Atoms / 1e9` using BigInt arithmetic, then `tao = alpha_tokens × price`. (3) Smoke target: mum_subnets <1% drift vs canonical 2.0095τ. (4) After patch lands, iter 176 = re-sweep all 4/7 wallets that previously returned shadow_ok. Expected outcomes: Subnets stays ≤0.5%, mum_subnets falls 54.89%→<1%, mum_smf + mum_mantat unchanged (already <3%, root-only so no share→token correction needed). ITER 174 SHIP: changelog-only commit, no lib/* code change. Tag: research (11th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168/169/170/171/172/173; 166 correctness interlude). Diff: lib/changelog-entries.js +N (this entry only). Pre-commit: `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. NOTES.md at ~/.openclaw/autonomous-agents/auto_c767d59b8f/NOTES.md updated with empirical tables + iter 175 patch spec + risk notes (TotalHotkeyShares storage name needs runtime-version confirmation if names changed since iter 167\'s SubnetTAO/SubnetAlphaIn enumeration). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
