    title: 'iter 172: pnlGroundTruth parallelizes Taostats + shadow paths via Promise.allSettled — shadow promise now kicks off at function entry alongside the Taostats rows/balance leg, and every return path (early-fail on tax_fetch_failed/no_tax_data/balance_fetch_failed/no_balance/no_balance_snapshots AND the success path) awaits + merges shadowFreeApi — unblocks the 6/7 coldkeys that iter 171 sweep got http:500 on because Taostats /price + /coldkey_alpha_shares 429s short-circuited pnlGroundTruth BEFORE the iter-170 shadow path could run; default-off prod cold path unchanged (when forceShadow=false AND FREE_PNL_SHADOW=0, shadowPromise is just Promise.resolve(null) — no RPC work, no latency added); drift only computed when canonical currentPortfolioTao exists (success path); failure paths surface ok+totalTao+freeTao+stakeTao without drift; sets up iter 173 = re-run 7-coldkey drift collector with parallel-fetch in place (should now succeed on all 7 regardless of Taostats availability) → iter 174 = graduate shadow→primary when Taostats heavy endpoints 429/5xx (priority #1 milestone)',
    body:
      'Iter 172. Refactors pnlGroundTruth so the shadow path runs IN PARALLEL with the Taostats leg instead of after it. Architectural change motivated directly by the iter 171 sweep CSV: 6 of 7 pinned coldkeys returned http:500 because Taostats /price + /coldkey_alpha_shares 429d during pnlGroundTruth\'s Taostats rows/balance fetch, taking the early-return at the tax_fetch_failed branch BEFORE the iter-169 inline shadow block could execute. That made shadow telemetry hostage to the exact upstream we\'re trying to escape — the opposite of what priority #1 needs. Mechanism: shadowPromise is constructed at the top of pnlGroundTruth (BEFORE the rows/balance fetch). When the shadow gate is on (forceShadow===true || process.env.FREE_PNL_SHADOW===\'1\'), shadowPromise wraps the existing Promise.race-with-5s-timeout around getColdkeyBalance(coldkey), with `.then(r => {ok:true, totalTao, freeTao, stakeTao, stakeAlpha, rpcCalls, latencyMs, wallClockMs, source})` and `.catch(err => {ok:false, error, wallClockMs, source})`. When the gate is off, shadowPromise = Promise.resolve(null) — zero RPC work, zero latency added to the default-off prod cold path. Every return path then `await`s shadowPromise and merges it into the response: (1) tax_fetch_failed/no_tax_data/balance_fetch_failed/no_balance early-return now includes shadowFreeApi (previously absent — that\'s the key fix); (2) no_balance_snapshots early-return likewise; (3) success path awaits shadowPromise and ALSO computes driftTao/driftPct against canonical currentPortfolioTao before merging (canonical only exists on success path). Why Promise.race-wrapped: preserves iter 169\'s 5s timeout so a finney intermittent failure can never extend pnlGroundTruth latency beyond Taostats\'s own. Why catch-all: pnlGroundTruth is load-bearing on every buildReport; a throw from the shadow path would break the parent computation. Why kick off at function entry not before Taostats fetch: function entry is before the preFetchedRows shortcut too, so the parallelism applies uniformly whether buildReport pre-fetches Taostats or pnlGroundTruth fetches inline. Pre-commit smoke: `node --check lib/report.js` PASSED; `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. Local smoke (npm install + smoke_iter172.mjs against pnlGroundTruth directly, both with rows:[] balance:null rowsFetchError:"mock 429" + forceShadow:true): case A (shadow off, taostats fail) returns {available:false, reason:"tax_fetch_failed", error:"mock 429", shadowFreeApi:null} — default-off preserved on failure path; case B (shadow ON, taostats fail) returns {available:false, reason:"tax_fetch_failed", error:"mock 429", shadowFreeApi:{ok:false,...}} where ok:false here is from a deliberately-malformed test coldkey (invalid checksum surfaces ok:false fast — structural goal proven: shadowFreeApi key NOW EXISTS on the failure path); case C (shadow ON, taostats OK with mocked rows+balance) returns {available:true, profitTao:..., shadowFreeApi:{...}} — shadow surfaces on success path too. The iter-169 behavior (success path shadow with drift) and iter-170 behavior (forceShadow opt threading) are both preserved. Diff: lib/report.js +52/-46 (shadowPromise hoisted to function entry, three return paths gain `await shadowPromise` + merge, old inline shadow block replaced by post-await drift computation), lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry). Bundle delta: 0 bytes. Why tag=research not feature: continues the priority #1 graduation arc (iter 167/168/169/170/171/172 all research; 166 was correctness interlude). 9th consecutive research tag. Verify wake plan: GH commit status success/Vercel, Playwright changelog top H2 starts with "iter 172: pnlGroundTruth parallelizes Taostats + shadow paths"; smoke probes: ?shadow=1 against an arbitrary coldkey — if Taostats happens to 429 in pnlGroundTruth\'s Taostats leg, the response should NOW include shadowFreeApi populated with ok+totalTao instead of available:false alone. Iter 173 plan: re-run 7-coldkey drift collector (same script as iter 171) — expect drift_pct populated on the 1 that previously succeeded AND ok+totalTao+freeTao+stakeTao on the 6 that previously http:500\'d (their pnlGroundTruth.available will still be false because Taostats may still 429, but shadowFreeApi will now surface). Iter 174 = graduate shadow→primary when Taostats heavy endpoints 429/5xx (priority #1 milestone). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
