    body:
      'Iter 171. First 7-coldkey drift telemetry sweep against the iter-170 /api/report?shadow=1 mechanism, executed as a sequential collector script with backoff/retry from VPS (no Vercel ship — this is changelog-only observability reporting; the iter is the EVIDENCE, not a code change). Canonical totals sourced from /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json portfolio (proven during iter 169 pre-flight). Method: for each pinned coldkey, POST /api/report?shadow=1 with -m 120 and parse shadowFreeApi.totalTao; compute drift_pct = |shadow - canonical| / canonical * 100. Results: (1) Subnets 5EKFph3D… → http:200, totalTao 5.4543τ (free 0.5006 + stake 4.9536) vs canonical 5.4593τ = **0.09% drift, wallClock 54ms**; (2) Mantat 5CTRC3sQ…ArLn → http:500 (pnlGroundTruth Taostats leg failed before shadow ran); (3) Root 5Cnz1juP… → http:500; (4) Mum Root 5FPhcFik… → http:500; (5) Mum SMF 5FzK9siZ… → http:500; (6) Mum Subnets 5GQAqusP… → http:500; (7) Mum Mantat 5HbWj5vb… → http:429. The 0.09% drift on Subnets is the strongest signal yet for priority #1 graduation: free-API stack matches canonical to within 0.005τ (50 quintillion rao on a 5.5τ balance) when the shadow path actually executes. WHY 6/7 didn\'t complete: the iter-170 shadow path runs INSIDE pnlGroundTruth AFTER the Taostats history+tax leg. When Taostats /api/price/latest/v1 or /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 throws (429/500), pnlGroundTruth returns available=false before the shadow path runs, so shadowFreeApi never populates. This is exactly the failure mode priority #1 graduation must address: when Taostats is degraded, we WANT the free-API path to take over, not be downstream of the failing Taostats call. Architectural implication for iter 172+: graduate the shadow path from "additive observability under FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1 / ?shadow=1" to "primary source when Taostats heavy endpoints return 429/5xx" (the priority #1 milestone). Concretely: pnlGroundTruth should attempt Taostats first; on retryable failure, attempt the free-API stack and surface its result under pnlGroundTruth (not shadowFreeApi). This is a 1-iter graduation but requires the drift telemetry across multiple coldkeys before declaring confidence — which is precisely what 6/7 today\'s Taostats degradation prevented. ALTERNATE iter 172: parallel-fetch Taostats AND free-API in pnlGroundTruth (Promise.allSettled) so the shadow path runs INDEPENDENTLY of Taostats leg — this would have unblocked all 7 coldkeys today and is arguably the right way to gather the rest of the drift baseline without depending on Taostats availability. Why not ship a code change this iter: we have one solid datapoint (0.09% drift) which is enough to anchor the iter 172 architectural decision; piling 6 more shadow paths into one ship without first proving the architectural fix would just produce more 500s. Iter 172 plan: refactor pnlGroundTruth so the shadow path runs in parallel with the Taostats leg (Promise.allSettled), not after it; then re-run the 7-coldkey sweep and report the full drift baseline. Tag: research (8th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168/169/170; 166 was correctness interlude). Diff: lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry only). Bundle delta: 0 bytes. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
