    body:
      'Iter 170. The iter-169 FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1 wire shipped as a process-env gate, which means activating it in prod needs a Vercel env push that pollutes ALL concurrent requests until it\'s cleaned up. For telemetry sweeps that just want to measure drift on one report at a time, that\'s a heavy hammer with a cleanup obligation. This iter adds a per-request override: POST /api/report?shadow=1 (with or without ?skipCache=1, which is implied) activates the shadow path for that single buildReport invocation. The override threads as opts.shadow through buildAndCacheReport → buildReport → pnlGroundTruth({ forceShadow }), and pnlGroundTruth\'s shadow gate becomes (forceShadow === true || process.env.FREE_PNL_SHADOW === \'1\') so either knob is sufficient. Cache safety: buildAndCacheReport explicitly skips the reportCache.set when opts.shadow===true, so a shadow build does NOT poison the cached non-shadow payload — a plain call right after a ?shadow=1 call rebuilds cleanly and returns shadowFreeApi: null as before. Route-side, ?shadow=1 also implies skipCache so a pre-existing cached non-shadow payload doesn\'t short-circuit the shadow build. Why this is the right shape for priority #1 graduation: the iter-167/168/169 arc built the free-API stack (freeRpc → freePnl → shadow surface) but kept it dormant. To DECIDE whether to graduate shadow→fallback (the priority #1 milestone), we need empirical drift telemetry across all 7 pinned coldkeys under prod buildReport conditions (Vercel egress, finney HTTPS RPC, real wallClock). Pre-iter-170, doing that required toggling Vercel env then running 7 sequential POSTs then untoggling the env — three side-effecting steps with cleanup risk. Post-iter-170, it\'s 7 plain POSTs to /api/report?shadow=1 from any caller, zero env pollution, zero cleanup. Why not a per-coldkey env (FREE_PNL_SHADOW_COLDKEY=5...): same env-toggle problem, plus tightly coupled to a single test wallet. Why not a header flag (X-Shadow: 1): we already parse search params for skipCache; consistency wins. Edge case: queryShadow defaults false on URL parse failure (same defensive try-catch as querySkip). Concurrent-request safety: forceShadow is a per-invocation function param, no global mutation — two concurrent /api/report calls (one ?shadow=1, one plain) won\'t cross-contaminate because each carries its own opts.shadow into its own pnlGroundTruth closure. The env-driven gate path is unchanged (env-true forces shadow on every call regardless of opts), so iter-169 behavior is fully preserved. Diff: lib/report.js +13/-3 (pnlGroundTruth signature gains forceShadow, gate condition widens, buildReport signature gains opts, callsite passes forceShadow, buildAndCacheReport gates the cache write); app/api/report/route.js +14/-1 (queryShadow parser + skipCache implication + opts threading). Bundle delta: 0 bytes. Why tag=research not feature: this is observability plumbing for a research milestone (priority #1 graduation), not a user-visible feature — same classification as iter 169. Smoke target after deploy: changelog top H2 starts with "/api/report gains a per-request ?shadow=1 URL-query"; tag badge reads "research" (7th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168/169; 166 was correctness interlude); regression smoke POST /api/report?skipCache=1 returns shadowFreeApi: null (proves the gate still respects the default-off env); shadow smoke POST /api/report?shadow=1 returns shadowFreeApi: { ok: true, totalTao, driftPct, ... } (proves the override actually flips the gate in prod). Pre-commit: `node --check lib/report.js` PASSED; `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED; `node --check app/api/report/route.js` PASSED. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
