    body:
      'Iter 169. Wires the iter-168 lib/freePnl.js getColdkeyBalance composer into lib/report.js pnlGroundTruth as an observability-only shadow layer behind FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1 env flag. The flag is OFF by default in production — this is research telemetry, not a behavior change. When the flag is set (locally, in preview deployments, or in a future Vercel env override), buildReport ALSO computes the free-API total_tao via three finney HTTPS RPC calls (1 state_getStorage System::Account for free balance + 1 state_call StakeInfoRuntimeApi for stake leg + 1 state_queryStorageAt batch for subnet pool reserves), measures drift against the Taostats-derived currentPortfolioTao, and surfaces both side-by-side in the response under pnlGroundTruth.shadowFreeApi. Shape: { ok: true, totalTao, freeTao, stakeTao, stakeAlpha, canonicalTao, driftTao, driftPct, rpcCalls, latencyMs: { free, stake, wallClock }, wallClockMs, source: "finney-rpc:freePnl" } on success; { ok: false, error, wallClockMs, source } on timeout/failure. Why Promise.race with 5s timeout: the free-API call is on the critical path of buildReport when FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1, and a finney rate-limit / cold connection could otherwise add 10-30s to every report build. 5s is comfortably above the observed 233-981ms VPS latency from the pre-flight validation suite. Why catch-all: pnlGroundTruth is load-bearing; any throw here would break the entire report. The catch returns { ok: false, error } so the AI prompt and frontend can detect-and-soft-omit the shadow surface without failing the parent computation. VPS pre-flight validation suite (2026-06-16T22:01Z, all 7 pinned coldkeys via /tmp/validate-7-coldkeys.mjs): 5Cnz1juP…SLbinH → 9.1856τ (free 0.0030, stake 9.1826) 757ms; 5CTRC3sQ…ArLn (Mantat) → 12.1188τ (free 0.2960, stake 11.8228) 981ms canonical 12.2766 drift 1.29%; 5EKFph3D…G5cd (Subnets) → 5.4526τ (free 0.5006, stake 4.9519) 471ms; 5FPhcFik…AedH → 51.8351τ (free 3.0000, stake 48.8351) 234ms; 5FzK9siZ…JcQzmm → 30.6950τ (free 0.0014, stake 30.6936) 233ms; 5GQAqusP…ap5cw2V → 3.1128τ (free 0.7556, stake 2.3572) 464ms; 5HbWj5vb…EjD1HL → 1.6438τ (free 0.2999, stake 1.3439) 462ms. Zero errors across 7 coldkeys, totalTao range 1.64τ–51.84τ all bounded + finite, latencies all well under the 5s timeout. The shadow surface is production-safe BEFORE first activation. Why FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1 specifically (not a feature flag in a config table): env flag matches the existing FREE_PNL=1 pattern (see iter 110), is per-deployment, and can be toggled via Vercel env without a code push. Iter 170+ can ramp: (a) enable in preview branch only, eyeball drift across a week of reports; (b) enable in prod for a single coldkey via env+coldkey gating; (c) graduate from shadow to fallback when Taostats /history/v1 + /tax/v1 are both 429/down (priority #1 graduation milestone). Why NOT default-on this iter: the load-bearing 7-of-N verify tally is the safety net for any report.js change; switching FREE_PNL_SHADOW on by default would add 233-981ms to every prod report build and could surface a finney intermittent failure as a buildReport regression. Shadow-mode OFF preserves the existing risk envelope (this iter is a no-op on the cold path) while the surface is dormant and ready. Pre-commit smoke: `node --check lib/report.js` PASSED; `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. Diff: 47 insertions / 1 deletion across 2 files (report.js +45/-1 for the shadow block + import + return key, changelog-entries.js +2 for the new entry). Bundle delta: 0 bytes (lib/freePnl.js was already importable via iter 168). Edge case: shadowFreeApi field is always present in the returned object (null when env flag is OFF) so downstream code can do `gt.shadowFreeApi?.ok` safely without optional-chaining gymnastics on a possibly-undefined key. Smoke target after deploy: changelog top H2 starts with "lib/report.js — FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1 env flag"; tag badge reads "research" (6th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168; 166 was correctness interlude); Subnets regression smoke verdict=matched + shadowFreeApi=null (env flag OFF in prod so the shadow surface should be present-but-null in the response). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
