    body:
      'Iter 168. Wires the three free-API legs (iter 164 free balance, iter 165 stake alpha decode, iter 167 price discovery + composer) into a single getColdkeyBalance(coldkey) entry point so future iters can shadow-mode and graduate the free-API stack against Taostats without further plumbing. Shape: returns `{ coldkey, totalTao, freeTao, stakeTao, stakeAlpha, latencyMs: { free, stake, wallClock }, rpcCalls, source: "finney-rpc:freePnl", legs: { free, stake } }`. The two underlying calls fire in parallel via Promise.all because they hit independent storage paths (System::Account vs StakeInfoRuntimeApi + SubtensorModule pool reserves) — wallClock therefore tracks the slower leg, not the sum. VPS validation this fire (Mantat coldkey 5CTRC3sQUTnPB6snh7LFAMCcWv6caMeFVmBhd78giH21ArLn): totalTao=12.1060τ, freeTao=0.2960τ, stakeTao=11.8100τ, stakeAlpha=280.3977α, 3 RPC calls (1 state_getStorage for free + 1 state_call for stake leg + 1 state_queryStorageAt for batched price leg), 1474ms wall clock. Canonical Mantat from /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json = 12.2766τ. Drift = 12.2766 − 12.1060 = 0.1706τ = 1.39%. This is BETTER than iter 167\'s stake-only validation (11.81τ vs 12.28τ = 3.81%) because iter 167 was measuring stake-only while the snapshot total includes free + stake. The remaining 1.39% drift is the snapshot-vs-live freshness window (subnet emissions + price drift since snapshot generation). No further price-leg or stake-leg work needed — drift is inherent to comparing live chain reads against a static snapshot. Why feature-flag-off / unwired: the priority #1 redirect calls for a "free-API PnL replacement" but the load-bearing surface in report.js is `pnlGroundTruth` (Taostats /tax/v1 transfer-flow derived profit), not just a current balance. Free balance is half the input to PnL — the missing half is transfers-in/transfers-out history, which the free RPC stack does NOT replicate (would need to scan every block since coldkey genesis, or use a free archive node API). Shipping getColdkeyBalance as a public surface today gives the next 1-2 iters a building block to: (a) shadow-mode `currentPortfolioSource: "delegation_snapshot"` fallback with free-API totalTao instead of waiting for Taostats /account/latest/v1 on the existing fallback path; (b) lay groundwork for a `pnlFreeApi` field that ONLY surfaces freeTao+stakeTao (no PnL formula) as a sanity check against the Taostats `currentPortfolio.total_tao`. Why no report.js wire-in this iter: keeps blast radius zero. Even a shadow-mode log adds Vercel egress latency (1-2s extra per buildReport call) and surfaces failure modes in a load-bearing code path. Defer to iter 169 with explicit "if FREE_PNL_SHADOW=1 env present, run shadow + log only" + the 7-coldkey validation suite. Pre-commit smoke: `node --check lib/freePnl.js` PASSED. Diff: 51 lines added (1 new file), 0 lines changed. Bundle delta: 0 bytes (pure re-export composition of existing freeRpc.js functions). Edge case: getColdkeyBalance returns the full `legs` payload so callers can introspect per-subnet stakeTao breakdown (legs.stake.byNetuid) and the raw freeRao / reservedRao (legs.free) without a second call. Includes a getColdkeyBalances(coldkeys[]) sequential helper for the 7-coldkey shadow-mode loop in iter 169 (sequential by design — finney rate-limits batched state_call calls on a per-IP basis, and 7 coldkeys × 2-3 calls each is well under the 16-calls-per-2s threshold from iter 167). Smoke target after deploy: changelog top H2 starts with "lib/freePnl.js — first per-coldkey total_tao composer"; tag badge reads "research" (5th consecutive after 163/164/165/167; 166 was a correctness interlude); Subnets regression smoke verdict=matched OR documented Taostats /price/latest/v1 still down (iter 167 verify surfaced /price/latest/v1 + /tax/v1 both timing out — selective Taostats degradation noted, NOT regression). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
