    body:
      'Iter 167. Closes the third and final leg of the free-API PnL ground-truth stack that started with iter 163 spike → iter 164 free-balance reader → iter 165 stake-leg reader. Discovery this fire: the storage map names guessed by the iter 165 wake notes were wrong — `SubtensorModule::TaoIn(netuid)` and `SubtensorModule::AlphaIn(netuid)` both return null on finney. VPS probe enumerated four candidates and the correct names are `SubnetTAO(netuid)` and `SubnetAlphaIn(netuid)`, both `StorageMap<_, Identity, u16, u64, ValueQuery>` so the storage key is `xxhash128("SubtensorModule") + xxhash128("SubnetTAO") + netuid_le_2bytes` (no per-key hash, just the raw 2-byte LE u16). Values are SCALE-encoded u64 LE rao-scaled. Price formula: `price[netuid] = SubnetTAO(netuid) / SubnetAlphaIn(netuid)` (TAO per α). Root netuid 0 has no AMM pool and the convention is 1.0 (1 α-root = 1 τ). Batching: tried sequential state_getStorage and hit finney HTTPS rate limit ("You are sending too many requests and are being rate limited. Consider running a local subtensor node if you need more!") after ~16 calls in 2 seconds — pivoted to state_queryStorageAt which fetches N×2 keys in one round-trip (Mantat 15 subnets × 2 keys = 30-key batch returned in 683ms). VPS validation suite ran this fire: (1) iterated 14 sampled subnets (Mantat canonical + a few additional), computed price = SubnetTAO/SubnetAlphaIn for each, compared to /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json `screener[].price` — 12/14 within 1% drift, most <0.3% (netuid 4 Targon 0.141%, netuid 5 Hone 0.031%, netuid 8 Apex-style 0.007%, netuid 9 0.046%, netuid 44 0.107%, netuid 51 0.091%, netuid 64 Chutes 0.072%); the 2 outliers (netuid 68 = 2.04%, netuid 95 = 1.19%) are higher-volatility subnets where live chain has drifted from snapshot freshness — both still acceptable for a ground-truth comparison. (2) Full Mantat alpha→TAO sum: decoded 16 stake entries via getColdkeyStakeAlpha, grouped by netuid, batched 30 pool keys via state_queryStorageAt, computed Σ(stakeAlpha × price) per (netuid). Result: 11.8085τ vs canonical 12.2766τ snapshot = 3.81% drift. Per-subnet prices match within 0.5% so the drift is dominated by snapshot freshness (canonical 12.2766τ was captured at api_snapshot.json generation time; live chain has accumulated emissions + price drift since). Acceptable as ground-truth validation. New exports: getSubnetPrices(netuids, opts) → { prices: {[netuid]: tao_per_alpha}, reserves: {[netuid]: {taoIn, alphaIn, taoInRao, alphaInRao}}, latencyMs, source, batchSize } and getColdkeyStakeTao(coldkey, opts) → { totalStakeTao, totalStakeAlpha, entries: [...{netuid, stakeAlpha, price, stakeTao, hotkey, ...}], byNetuid: [...{netuid, stakeAlpha, stakeTao, price, hotkeyCount}], prices, reserves, rpcCalls: 2, latencyMs: { stake, prices, total }, poolKeyBatchSize, source, note }. Internal helpers: subnetPoolKey(item, netuid) and decodeU64LE(hex) exported via __internals for test access. Why two RPC calls is the magic number: getColdkeyStakeTao = 1 state_call (stake leg) + 1 state_queryStorageAt (price leg, batched). 0 paid Taostats API calls. Roughly 1.5-2.0s total round-trip from VPS, likely 1-2.5s from Vercel egress on warm invokes. Why stays feature-flagged off: this is leg 3 of 3 for the ground-truth replacement, but the full validation surface (matching Taostats getLatestBalance + delegationSnapshot across all 7 pinned coldkeys, not just Mantat) hasn\'t been run in shadow mode yet. Iter 168 = wire getFreeBalance + getColdkeyStakeTao into a unified getColdkeyBalance(coldkey) function and add a shadow-mode FREE_PNL=1 env flag that logs the free-API result alongside Taostats and surfaces the drift in the report response (without replacing Taostats). Iter 169+ = expand validation to all 7 coldkeys, compare drift distributions, then graduate to a fallback path when Taostats throws 429. Pre-commit smoke: `node --check lib/freeRpc.js` PASSED. Zero production code path touched (lib/report.js unchanged, lib/taostats.js unchanged); the 7-of-7 verify tally has zero risk surface from this iter. Diff: ~95 lines added to lib/freeRpc.js, 0 lines changed. Bundle delta: 0 bytes (uses already-installed @polkadot/util + @polkadot/util-crypto from iter 164). Edge case considered: dead/empty subnets where SubnetAlphaIn = 0 → price returned as 0 (handled by `alphaIn > 0n` guard); inactive netuids (no storage value) → decodeU64LE handles hex === "0x" → 0n → same path. Root netuid 0 has no pool storage at all → hardcoded 1.0 convention. Smoke target after deploy: confirm changelog top H2 starts with "lib/freeRpc.js gains the price leg"; tag badge reads "research" (4th consecutive after 163/164/165); Subnets regression smoke returns verdict=matched (lib/freeRpc.js stays unused, pure additive ship). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days).',
