    title: 'app/api/report/route.js now reads skipCache from BOTH the JSON body and the URL query string (?skipCache=1) — repairs a silent measurement-integrity bug that has been corrupting verify-wake regression smokes since iter 162: every "skipCache=1" probe issued as a URL query param was being IGNORED by the route (which only checked body?.skipCache === true), so a single poisoned cache entry from one upstream timeout would return cached failures on every subsequent smoke until the TTL expired, producing the false "tax_fetch_failed regression across two consecutive probes" alert that iter 165 verify logged as a 7-of-7-broken warning when the underlying app was actually healthy (a body-skipCache probe this fire returned verdict=matched / profit=-0.190τ / source=taostats /api/accounting/tax/v1 in 39s, matching iter 164 exactly)',
    body:
      'Iter 166. Pivot from the planned stake-leg iter (per-subnet alpha→TAO conversion) to a measurement-integrity fix that is higher leverage than any single-leg research advance, because every verify wake from iter 162 onward has been depending on a broken skipCache mechanism. Setup: iter 165 verify (2026-06-16T19:06Z) reported `pnlGroundTruth.available=False reason="tax_fetch_failed"` on Subnets `5EKFph3D…G5cd` across TWO consecutive `skipCache=1` probes — flagged as the first verdict regression in ~7+ iters and logged as iter-166 precondition. iter 166 fire decision-tree probed Taostats `/api/accounting/tax/v1` directly from the VPS against four canonical coldkeys (Subnets 312 rows / 597ms, Mantat 1403 rows / 718ms, Root 252 rows / 469ms, Mum_mantat 358 rows / 450ms — ALL http:200 healthy) confirming the upstream was fine. Re-ran the Vercel smoke and immediately reproduced the 504/61s timeout that ORIGINALLY poisoned the cache during the iter 165 verify pass. The next two probes returned http:200 in 0.5s / 0.3s with `cached: true` and the same `reason: "tax_fetch_failed"` — every subsequent `?skipCache=1` probe was being SERVED FROM THE POISONED CACHE because the route handler only checks `body?.skipCache === true` (route.js:60). Final probe with `skipCache:true` in the JSON body returned 200 / 39.4s / `available: true` / `source: "taostats /api/accounting/tax/v1"` / `verdict: matched` / `profit: -0.19025865τ` — IDENTICAL to iter 164\'s verdict=matched figures, proving the underlying app never regressed. The 7-of-7 verdict tally was NEVER broken in iter 165. Implementation: app/api/report/route.js gains a `querySkip` helper that safely parses `req.url` into a URL and reads `searchParams.get(\'skipCache\') === \'1\'`, then defines `skipCache = body?.skipCache === true || querySkip`. Safe fallback `catch { return false }` in case req.url is malformed (defensive — should never throw in practice). Why this is correctness not polish: the iter-47 redirect parks polish backlog because polish doesn\'t move the load-bearing priorities; but a broken skipCache mechanism corrupts the verify methodology we use to validate every iter\'s landing, including the stake-leg research iters that comprise the actual priority #1 arc. Iter 166 ships before iter 167 (stake-leg per-subnet alpha→TAO conversion) because honest measurement is a precondition for honest research progress. Why a tiny diff: 12 lines added to route.js, zero behaviour change for any caller that already sends `skipCache: true` in the body (body-skipCache still works exactly as before — the new querySkip is OR\'d in, never replaces). Why no changelog noise on the URL-query semantics: `?skipCache=1` is a dev/verify-only flag, not a public API; production callers (the Personalised Report tab UI in the cockpit) always POST a JSON body and never set skipCache. The change is invisible to users; visible to wake scripts. Cache-poisoning recovery: the poisoned Subnets entry will heal itself the moment any caller (including the iter 166 verify wake) hits the route with `?skipCache=1` after deploy — the new branch will see querySkip=true, route to `buildAndCacheReport()` instead of `peekCachedReport()`, overwrite the entry with a fresh successful result. No manual cache invalidation needed. Why this isn\'t a route-handler refactor: kept the diff bounded to the skipCache lookup, did not touch rate-limit logic, route shape, error paths, or the GET handler. Pre-commit smoke target: route shape unchanged (`POST /api/report` still validates SS58, still rate-limits cache-misses, still returns the same JSON shape). Post-deploy smoke target: Subnets `5EKFph3D839fxdbQwhAHyM4CQzBHNpLSecUAteNZKqW1G5cd` with `?skipCache=1` as a URL query param (NO body change needed) — IDEAL = http:200 + pnlGroundTruth.available=true + verdict=matched + profit=-0.190τ + cached=null. Confirms (a) the URL-query path works, (b) the previously poisoned cache slot was overwritten, (c) the 7-of-7 verdict tally is intact and was never actually broken. Wake-prompt note: the wake-prompt decision tree assumed the iter 165 regression was real; this fire\'s probe disproves that premise. The "(A) Taostats /tax/v1 working" branch was the correct path but the right ship is the measurement-integrity fix not the stake leg — stake leg defers to iter 167 with a clean verify baseline. Memory recommendation: append note to `lessons_skipcache_actually_wired.md` (already documents the "always check cached field before debugging" rule) — extend with "verify wakes pre-iter-166 used `?skipCache=1` URL param which the route silently ignored; any regression alert from those wakes is a measurement artifact not a real regression unless reproduced with body-skipCache". PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
