    body:
      'Iter 161. Targets the 7-of-7 milestone after iter 160 restored 3 wallets in one shot (Subnets, Root, Mum_mantat all matched ✓ via stale-OK getBalanceHistory cache). Mantat is the last holdout: iter 142 verify ran 504/60.8s with FUNCTION_INVOCATION_TIMEOUT and no JSON body, unchanged through every iter since 157 because all prior fixes targeted same-bucket throttle collisions (155 Phase B, 156 retry widening, 157 inter-page delay) but compounded the latency floor. Diagnosis from iter 157\'s 200ms inter-page delay + iter 156\'s [1500, 4000, 10000] retry budget: getDelegationHistory paginates a multi-page chain for Mantat (12.28τ across many netuids), each page-fetch consumes ~2-5s of retry budget on warm/recovered buckets, but a later-page 429 can exhaust the full ~15.5s retry schedule, and with N pages already eaten ~40-50s the throw lands past the 60s ceiling as a Vercel timeout instead of as a clean 500 JSON. The wider per-call retries CAN\'T fix this — they ARE the problem when accumulated across pages. The fix is a cumulative cap: track `Date.now() - startedAt` at the top of each loop iteration; if elapsed > DELEGATION_HISTORY_BUDGET_MS (30s, chosen to leave the rest of buildReport ~25s of headroom under Vercel\'s 60s maxDuration), break the loop with `truncated=true, truncationReason="budget_exceeded"` and return partial rows. Also wrap the taoGet call in try/catch: if page > 1 throws (mid-pagination 429 after exhausting retries), return partial instead of bubbling — page-1 throws still bubble unchanged (preserves iter 154 lying-catch fix; we never want to mask a total fetch failure as an empty-array success). Partial flag attached as non-enumerable `partial`, `partialReason`, `pagesFetched` properties on the returned array so the array iterates identically to the full-data case in downstream consumers (lib/report.js:2285 just does `const history = await getDelegationHistory(coldkey)` and iterates), but the metadata is available to anyone who wants to inspect it. Why non-enumerable: keeps the shape lossless for the buildReport pipeline (no signature change, no destructure surprise) while giving observability via `history.partial` for callers who care. Why 30s vs other windows: Vercel\'s 60s maxDuration is the hard ceiling, buildReport\'s other sections (yield, screener, FX, pnlGroundTruth, taxYearSection) typically consume 15-25s combined on Mantat-tier wallets; 30s for delegation history leaves ~5s of slack under the ceiling on the worst path. Why this is the structural fix iters 156/157 were dancing around: pure retry widening (156) and pure inter-page delays (157) both INCREASE the latency floor per page; the budget cap is the first knob that BOUNDS total time spent in this one function regardless of how badly throttling cascades. Trade-off honest: partial-data PnL is less complete than full-history PnL — for Mantat, this means the pnlGroundTruth path will see only the first N pages of delegation events, so `lifetimeIn`/`lifetimeOut` will be undercounted, and sheet parity will diverge. But partial PnL with a `partial:true` annotation is strictly better than no JSON (which iter 142 verify proved is what Mantat returns today). iter 162 candidate if this surfaces partial PnL but parity divergence: switch consumers to read `history.partial` and emit a verdict like "partial_history" instead of "matched/harvest/accumulation" so the user sees the truncation. For other multi-page wallets (Subnets at fire 2 ran 40s end-to-end so getDelegationHistory likely consumed ~15-20s — well under 30s cap, no effect), the cap NEVER fires on the happy path, only on degraded throttle conditions. Non-regressive for the 5 already-verified happy-path wallets and the 3 iter-160-restored wallets: the budget check is a single subtraction + comparison per loop iteration, the try/catch around taoGet adds zero overhead when no throw occurs, and the partial-flag attachment only runs when truncated=true. Mum_mantat (verified at 56s, lifetimeIn=0/lifetimeOut=0 = zero delegation pages) fires the budget check zero times because `rows.length < 200 on page 1 → break` — no risk to the brittle wallet. Pre-commit smoke: node --check on both files passed, export shape preserved (getDelegationHistory still a function, no API call needed to validate structure). Post-deploy smoke target: Mantat 5CTRC3sQUTnPB6snh7LFAMCcWv6caMeFVmBhd78giH21ArLn (canonical per /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json) — IDEAL outcome: http:200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and either a sheet-parity verdict (if all pages fit under 30s) or a "partial_history" verdict (if budget fired, surfaced via history.partial). Either way, NO MORE 504. Three scenarios per smoke: (a) IDEAL — http:200, verdict landed (matched/harvest/accumulation OR partial_history), tally 6→7 of 7 milestone HIT; (b) PARTIAL BUT NO VERDICT — http:200 with rows present but the downstream pnlGroundTruth/taxYearSection code doesn\'t handle partial gracefully, iter 162 adjusts the verdict path to read history.partial; (c) STILL 504 — budget cap insufficient, iter 162 shrinks to 25s OR moves delegation into iter 160\'s cache pattern (cache by coldkey, 5min stale-OK on /api/delegation/v1). Cache pattern likely needed eventually because partial data still recomputes from scratch on every cold-start fire; for now, breaking the 60s ceiling is the priority. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
