    body:
      'Iter 159. Direct rollback + structural fix after iter 158 verify (2026-06-16T11:09Z) produced NEGATIVE NET outcome: tally regressed 5-of-7 → 4-of-7. Setup: iter 158 chained latestBalanceP after balanceSeriesP with a 200ms inter-call delay, hypothesising the two parallel `/api/account/history/v1` fires were colliding in lockstep on the per-IP throttle bucket. Verify evidence refuted that hypothesis: Subnets 5EKFph3D…G5cd (matched ✓ since iter 149) regressed to http:200/37.0s with `pnlGroundTruth.reason="balance_fetch_failed"` and `error="Taostats /api/account/history/v1 → 429"` — the chained pattern, by burning balanceSeriesP\'s entire retry budget FIRST, left the throttle bucket strictly more depleted by the time latestBalanceP fired 200ms later; the bucket couldn\'t recover in 200ms so latestBalanceP started attempt 1 against an already-exhausted bucket and surfaced the 429. Mum_mantat 5HbWj5vb…jD1HL still failed (http:200/56.1s, reason="tax_fetch_failed", error="/api/account/history/v1 → 429") — the failure label SHIFTED from balance_fetch_failed (iter 157) to tax_fetch_failed (iter 158), because the chained pattern delayed the balance-error surface long enough that the tax-FY for-loop\'s own /history/v1 retries got into the catch first. Diagnosis: chaining same-endpoint calls is the WRONG primitive. Throttle buckets are stateful per-IP per-endpoint; sequential calls on an exhausted bucket fail identically to parallel calls. The only fix that actually works is to NOT make the second call at all. Read lessons_taostats_account_endpoints.md: "/account/history/v1 is daily snapshots" — getBalanceHistory paginates the SAME endpoint that getLatestBalance hits, and getBalanceHistory\'s `out` array is sorted ascending by timestamp (lib/taostats.js:699 explicit `out.sort((a, b) => new Date(a.timestamp) - new Date(b.timestamp))`), so the LAST row of balanceSeries IS the most-recent daily snapshot — identical freshness to a separate getLatestBalance call to the same endpoint. The fix: in buildReport, replace the chained latestBalanceP with `const lastSeriesRow = balanceSeries[balanceSeries.length - 1]` and shape-map `{timestamp → snapshotAt, totalTao, stakedTao}` so the downstream pnlGroundTruth consumer sees the exact same {stakedTao, totalTao, snapshotAt} shape getLatestBalance returned. One call replaces two. Error capture: balanceSeriesP\'s `.catch(() => [])` now captures the error into the same `latestBalanceError` variable that gets threaded into pnlGroundTruth via `balanceFetchError` — iter 154 lying-catch fix preserved. Why no functional regression: per lessons_taostats_account_endpoints.md, /api/account/history/v1 ALREADY lags up to 24h (daily snapshots), so deriving from the last row vs calling getLatestBalance separately yields the same freshness (both hit the same endpoint, both return the same most-recent daily snapshot). Shape-match handled in the remap layer. Why Mum_mantat\'s brittle bound IMPROVES: was 56.8s at iter 157 firing two /history/v1 calls in lockstep, 56.1s at iter 158 firing them chained with 200ms delay. iter 159 fires ONE call. Estimated latency drop: removes ~3-5s of redundant getLatestBalance call + retry overhead, putting Mum_mantat at ~52-53s — more headroom under Vercel\'s 60s ceiling than at any point since iter 154. Bonus: removes 1 entire /history/v1 call from EVERY wallet\'s critical path (-1 endpoint hit per /api/report invocation). For high-throughput Vercel cold-starts where Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys re-fetch within the same minute, that\'s 7 fewer /history/v1 calls per minute = 50% reduction in this endpoint\'s footprint. Pre-commit smoke target: re-probe Mum_mantat (IDEAL = harvest_preferred verdict landed → 5-of-7 restored), Subnets (IDEAL = matched ✓ verdict restored → 6-of-7 restored), and ideally one happy-path wallet like Root to confirm no regression elsewhere. Three scenarios per wallet: (a) IDEAL — http:200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and sheet-parity verdict landed, proves the rollback restored both regressed wallets; (b) STILL BLOCKED — http:200 with reason="balance_fetch_failed" and the same /history/v1 → 429 error, proves the single getBalanceHistory call ALSO hits the throttle bare and needs further work (iter 160 candidate: server-side cache on getBalanceHistory mirror of iter 146 price cache, since /history/v1 is daily snapshots = high cacheability); (c) FRESH BLOCKER — different endpoint surfaces, log it. ALTERNATE if Mum_mantat lands but balance shape mismatch breaks downstream (would be a bug): the remap to {stakedTao, totalTao, snapshotAt} should be lossless because getBalanceHistory rows are already in that exact data — verify via the smoke fire pnlGroundTruth output. ALTERNATE if Mantat\'s /delegation/v1 → 429 still blocks (independent path, not affected by iter 159): iter 160 = cumulative pagination budget cap inside getDelegationHistory\'s while-loop with partial-data fallback. Trade-off honest: derived latestBalance gives daily-snapshot freshness (same as getLatestBalance for /account/history/v1, which is the endpoint both call). Some callers MIGHT have wanted live block-level freshness — but the buildReport code path was already on /history/v1 via getLatestBalance, not on /account/latest/v1, so there\'s no freshness regression. Non-regressive for the 5 already-verified wallets + iter 154 error-capture pattern: balanceSeriesP\'s catch now sets latestBalanceError just like the old latestBalanceP did, preserving the iter 154 reason="balance_fetch_failed" branch in pnlGroundTruth. getLatestBalance is STILL imported (line 13) and used by the legacy pnlGroundTruth fallback path (line 198) for non-prefetched callers — that path is untouched. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
