    body:
      'Iter 158. Direct restoration of Mum_mantat verdict after iter 157 verify (2026-06-16T10:08Z) exposed a NEW failure mode hiding behind the wider [1500, 4000, 10000] retry budget. Setup: iter 157 verify re-probed Mum_mantat 5HbWj5vb…jD1HL (the brittle 56s-near-Vercel-ceiling wallet that iter 154 verified with harvest_preferred verdict via paid tax/v1 path). Result: http:200/56.8s, but `pnlGroundTruth.available=false`, `reason="balance_fetch_failed"`, `error="Taostats /api/account/history/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later."` — first prod proof of iter 154 try/catch firing (dispositive evidence the architecture is sound), but the verdict was lost. Initial hypothesis (per wake-prompt iter 158 plan): widen /api/account/history/v1 in TAOSTATS_PATH_RETRY_WAITS. Investigation refuted that — the path was ALREADY widened to [1500, 4000, 10000] back in iter 153 (~15.5s cumulative). So why did it 429 with the wider budget? Read the buildReport code path (lib/report.js:2296+2304 pre-fix): two independent Promises both calling /api/account/history/v1 — `balanceSeriesP = getBalanceHistory(coldkey, 730)` paginates the endpoint over 2 years of daily snapshots, `latestBalanceP = getLatestBalance(coldkey)` calls the same endpoint with limit=1 page=1. Both fired at the same tick of the event loop (no await between them), both hit Vercel\'s shared egress IP at t=0, both collided on the per-IP throttle bucket for that endpoint, both 429\'d on attempt 1. Their retries scheduled in lockstep (both wait 1500ms, both fire at t=1500, both 429), then again at t=5500 (1500+4000), then again at t=15500 (1500+4000+10000) — both calls consumed the entire wider retry budget in lockstep WITHOUT making progress, because every attempt collided with the other. Wider retries CAN\'T fix this — adding more attempts just extends the collision window. The fix: chain latestBalanceP\'s Promise after balanceSeriesP settles, with a 200ms delay between. `const latestBalanceP = balanceSeriesP.then(() => new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 200))).then(() => getLatestBalance(coldkey).catch(...))`. Fine-grained mirror of iter 155 Phase B serialisation pattern (Phase B serialised cross-endpoint same-host calls; iter 158 serialises same-endpoint same-host calls). The downstream `await balanceSeriesP` and `await latestBalanceP` at the bottom of the section are unchanged — the chained Promise resolves at its natural time, so the tax-FY for-loop still overlaps both. Why 200ms (vs iter 155\'s 75ms inter-call): /api/account/history/v1 per-IP throttle window is empirically longer than the cross-endpoint window iter 155 hit — iter 157 verify proved 200ms inter-page worked inside getDelegationHistory for the same throttle class. Bounded overhead: ~200ms added to total latency, since balanceSeriesP paginates over ~2 years of history already (typically 8-15s for a multi-page wallet), and latestBalanceP\'s single call (~1-2s warm, ~3-4s with retry budget) now starts after that completes instead of in parallel. Mum_mantat impact: was 56s at the ceiling, now estimated 58s — STILL within 60s but tighter by 2s. The trade-off is honest: 200ms inter-call delay is necessary for verdict landing, AND the actual latestBalanceP call now waits its full natural latency after balanceSeriesP. Lower-risk wallets (Subnets, Root, Mum_smf, Mum_root, Mum_subnets — the 5 already-verified) get +200ms uniformly; Mantat (still blocked on /api/delegation/v1 per iter 157, deferred to iter 159) is unchanged. Why not derive latestBalance from balanceSeries\'s last row to eliminate the second /history/v1 call entirely: balanceSeries pulls daily snapshots from the same endpoint, but getLatestBalance uses limit=1 page=1 which returns the LIVE balance (not the most-recent daily snapshot, which can lag up to 24h). The two calls return different shapes — refactoring to use balanceSeries\'s last row would lose live freshness AND require shape-conversion in pnlGroundTruth\'s consumer. iter 158 keeps both calls and just serialises them. Smoke target: re-probe Mum_mantat — IDEAL = http:200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and harvest_preferred or matched verdict landed (mirror of iter 154\'s baseline). Bonus check: also re-probe one happy-path wallet (e.g. Subnets) to confirm no regression on the 200ms global add. ALTERNATE if Mum_mantat still 429s on /api/account/history/v1: throttle window is even longer than 200ms, widen to 500ms. ALTERNATE if Mum_mantat lands but elapsed jumps past 60s: drop the 200ms delay to 100ms, or move balanceSeriesP into Phase B above (sequential before tax-FY loop). Non-regressive for the 5 already-verified wallets: shape returned by latestBalanceP unchanged, error-capture pattern from iter 154 unchanged. Mantat fix deferred to iter 159 (cumulative pagination budget cap inside getDelegationHistory, or partial-data fallback). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
