    tag: 'reliability',
    title: 'buildReport now serialises its Taostats calls (getTaoPrice → getHoldings → getDelegationHistory) with a 75ms inter-request delay, while the non-Taostats hosts (tao.app screener, open.er-api.com FX) stay parallel — direct unblock for Mantat (/api/delegation/v1 → 429) and Mum_subnets (/api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 → 429), the 2 of Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys still failing the iter 142 verify sweep because the old top-level Promise.all fired three Taostats calls in parallel from Vercel\'s shared egress IP and collided with the per-IP throttle bucket',
    body:
      'Iter 155. Direct unblock of the 2 remaining wallets in the iter 142 retroactive verify sweep. Setup: iter 150 dispositively traced both failures to per-endpoint 429s — Mantat 500/6.7s with error "/api/delegation/v1 → 429: Rate Limited" and Mum_subnets 500/5.7s with error "/api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 → 429: Rate Limited". Both failures fired the default [1500, 3500] retry schedule before throwing, so each call exhausted its per-endpoint budget. Diagnosis: getHoldings (/api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares) and getDelegationHistory (/api/delegation/v1) were firing concurrently in buildReport\'s top-level Promise.all alongside getTaoPrice (/api/price/latest/v1) — three Taostats calls leaving Vercel\'s shared egress IP at the same millisecond. The Taostats per-IP throttle is global across endpoints within a burst window, so the parallel triple-fire collided with itself and each call independently 429\'d on its own first attempt. Iter 149 + iter 153 widened backoffs are useless against this because the retries themselves keep colliding with each other (the other two calls are still in-flight when one retries). The fix: split the Promise.all into two phases — Phase A keeps tao.app screener + open.er-api.com FX parallel (different hosts, no collider with Taostats), Phase B serialises getTaoPrice → getHoldings → getDelegationHistory with a 75ms inter-request delay between each, so each Taostats request gets the IP to itself for the duration of its retry chain. Why serialise only the Taostats bucket and not all five calls: getSubnetScreener (tao.app) and getUsdToAud (open.er-api.com) hit entirely different hosts with their own rate limits, parallelising them with the Taostats sequence costs nothing and saves ~1-2s of cold-start latency. Why 75ms delay between Taostats calls: Taostats per-IP throttle window appears to be sub-second based on iter 150 evidence; 75ms is enough to defeat tight bursts without meaningfully padding the report latency. Trade-off honest: the sequential Taostats sequence adds latency where the old parallel triple-fire would have completed in max(price, holdings, history). For a healthy fetch with no retries: ~250ms (price, cached often) + 75ms + ~2-5s (holdings, paged) + 75ms + ~2-10s (history, paged) ≈ 4-15s typical, vs old parallel max ≈ 2-10s. Adds 2-5s typical latency. For Mum_mantat which iter 154 verified at 56s (right at Vercel\'s 60s maxDuration), this WILL move it closer to the ceiling — the brittle-regression risk Jai flagged is real. Mitigation if Mum_mantat regresses into timeout: iter 156 can pivot to (a) shrink the delay to 25-50ms, (b) parallelise getTaoPrice with the non-Taostats phase since it\'s cached 60s and rarely re-fetches, or (c) cap a maxTotalRetryBudget across the buildReport stack. Pre-commit smoke 4/4 PASS: Phase A parallel calls fire concurrently, Phase B Taostats sequence is sequential (await between each), 75ms delays present and equal between price/holdings and holdings/history, downstream consumers (portfolio, pnl, pnlGroundTruth, taxYearSection) receive identical inputs to before — no signature change, no shape change. iter 147 + 149 + 151 + 153 + 154 wiring all intact (only the top-level fetch ordering changes). Post-deploy smoke target: re-probe Mantat 5CTRC3sQUTnPB6snh7LFAMCcWv6caMeFVmBhd78giH21ArLn + Mum_subnets 5GQAqusPNfe7qbtzXdpv6PcbgxQDG7K3nVwzmLPQKap5cw2V (canonical coldkeys verified against /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json per lessons_wake_prompt_coldkeys_unsafe.md). IDEAL outcome: both http:200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and sheet-parity verdicts — 7-of-7 milestone complete (the entire iter 142 retroactive verify sweep done). ALTERNATE if either still 429s: pivot iter 156 to widen TAOSTATS_PATH_RETRY_WAITS to cover both endpoints with the [1500, 4000, 10000] schedule (mirror iter 149/153 pattern). ALTERNATE if Mum_mantat regresses into timeout: shrink the inter-request delay to 25ms or move getTaoPrice into Phase A. Non-regressive for the 5 wallets already verified — buildReport signature and return shape unchanged, only the internal fetch ordering changes. KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — collider/fanout fix, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
