    title: 'Free-path /api/account/history/v1 and /api/transfer/v1 now get the wider [1500, 4000, 10000] retry schedule (~15.5s cumulative) too — direct unblock for Mum_root, the wallet iter 152 proved the iter 151 auto-fallback fires for in production but whose free-path first-call (account/history/v1) was itself 429-throttled past the default 5s cumulative wait, so the iter 142 sheet-parity verdict still couldn\'t land',
    body:
      'Iter 153. Direct unblock of the lying-fallback path iter 152 surfaced. Setup: iter 151 wired paid /api/accounting/tax/v1 to auto-fall-back into the free-tier /api/account/history/v1 + /api/transfer/v1 reconstruction (getTaxReportRangeFree) whenever retries exhaust. Iter 152 ran the re-sweep on Mum_root + Mum_mantat (the other 2 tax_fetch_failed wallets from iter 150) and produced the dispositive evidence: Mum_root probe returned 200/41.2s with reason:"tax_fetch_failed" + error:"Taostats /api/account/history/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." The error string names the FREE-path endpoint, not paid /tax/v1, which is only physically possible if (1) paid retries exhausted, (2) try/catch caught the throw, (3) getTaxReportRangeFree was invoked, (4) its first call (account/history/v1) also 429\'d — and the 41.2s elapsed vs iter 149\'s 23s baseline is consistent with the full chain firing. iter 151 fallback wiring is therefore PROVEN in production; the new unfixed problem is that the free-path endpoints can ALSO be Vercel-egress 429\'d, with the same per-IP-range throttle window that exceeds the default [1500, 3500] = ~5s cumulative wait. Iter 153 ships the symmetric fix to iter 149: extend TAOSTATS_PATH_RETRY_WAITS to map /api/account/history/v1 and /api/transfer/v1 to the same [1500, 4000, 10000] schedule (3 retries, ~15.5s cumulative wait) iter 149 gave paid tax/v1. Same shape, same retryWaitsFor() helper, same _getTaostatsRetryWaitsFor test accessor — strictly additive. Why these two endpoints only: getTaxReportRangeFree (lib/taostats.js:443) makes exactly two endpoint-types of calls — paginated /api/account/history/v1 to reconstruct the snapshot rows, plus /api/transfer/v1 to merge in transfer_in/transfer_out events. Both run via taoGet, both inherit the per-path retry schedule. Other paths (/api/delegation/v1, /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1, /api/account/latest/v1, /api/price/latest/v1) deliberately keep the default schedule — they\'re orthogonal blockers (delegation + alpha_shares are a fanout-burst problem that wider retries paper over rather than fix; latest balance has its own iter-154 candidate lying-catch issue; price has the iter-146 server cache so retries don\'t matter much). Pre-commit smoke 12/12 PASS: iter-149 tax/v1 still returns [1500, 4000, 10000], iter-153 history/v1 returns wider, iter-153 transfer/v1 returns wider, unmapped /price/latest falls back to [1500, 3500], balance endpoint untouched, delegation untouched, completely unknown path falls back, widened cumulative = 15500ms, default cumulative = 5000ms, widened = 3 retries / default = 2 retries, widened monotonically increasing. iter 144 timeout map intact, iter 146 price-cache exports intact (_resetTaoPriceCache + _getTaoPriceCacheState still exported), iter 151 fallback wiring intact (try/catch wrap, FREE_PNL_FALLBACK=0 escape hatch preserved, getTaxReportRangeFree still exported). Trade-off honest: a free-path call that 429s on all 4 attempts now wastes ~15.5s more before throwing — so a wallet where BOTH paid /tax/v1 AND free /account/history/v1 are 429-throttled on Vercel-egress could spend ~31s on retries alone (15.5s paid + 15.5s free) before the fallback verdict surfaces. Worst-case still fits inside Vercel\'s 60s maxDuration with ~25s headroom for the actual work. But the alternative is the iter 152 status quo: paid 429 → catch → free 429 → fail in ~5s with a verdict that lies about the cause. Iter 153 trades ~10s of additional retry latency for the verdict actually landing. Smoke-verify plan post-deploy: re-probe Mum_root 5FPhcFi…AedH with skipCache=1, expected outcomes — (a) IDEAL: 200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and a sheet-parity verdict (4-of-7 milestone, FIRST wallet to land iter 142 verify via free-path reconstruction); (b) STILL BLOCKED: 200 with tax_fetch_failed + error string from one of /account/history/v1 or /transfer/v1 + elapsed ≥50s — proof the wider retries fired on the free-path but the throttle window genuinely exceeds 15.5s, pivot iter 154 to balance lying-catch fix (Mum_mantat unblock, independent path); (c) PAID SUCCEEDED: bonus iter 142 verdict via paid path (Taostats throttle cleared in interim, fallback didn\'t need to fire). Non-regressive: every existing endpoint keeps its prior schedule, only the two named free-path endpoints get the wider treatment. taoGet signature unchanged, all callers transparent to the per-path config. KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — calibration/reliability fix, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
