    title: 'Paid /api/accounting/tax/v1 now auto-falls-back to the free-tier /api/account/history/v1 + /api/transfer/v1 reconstruction whenever it throws after retries are exhausted — so the 3 of Jai\'s 5 unverified pinned coldkeys (Mum_root, Mum_smf, Mum_mantat) that iter 150 verify confirmed were still 429-throttling on Vercel-egress past iter 149\'s widened backoff finally get a real iter 142 sheet-parity verdict instead of "tax_fetch_failed"; FREE_PNL=1 stays as the explicit opt-in for paid-skip, FREE_PNL_FALLBACK=0 disables the auto-fallback if Jai needs to expose raw paid throws for diagnostics',
    body:
      'Iter 151. Direct unblock of the 3 remaining tax_fetch_failed wallets from iter 150\'s retroactive iter 142 verify sweep. Setup: iter 149 widened the /api/accounting/tax/v1 retry schedule to [1500, 4000, 10000] (~15.5s cumulative wait, 3 retries vs default 2) and landed the headline win on Subnets — first non-Root coldkey to confirm iter 142 sheet-parity verdict (matched ✓, divergence 0.000τ, 193 tax rows fetched where iter 147 baseline got 0). Iter 150 ran the full sweep on the remaining 5 coldkeys spaced ≥13s apart and produced a clean diagnostic table: 3 of 5 (Mum_root, Mum_smf, Mum_mantat) still returned reason:"tax_fetch_failed" with error "Taostats /api/accounting/tax/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." even after iter 149\'s widened backoff fired its full ~15.5s cumulative wait across 4 attempts. Diagnosis: the Taostats per-IP throttle window on Vercel\'s shared egress range sometimes exceeds 15.5s when the IP has been cold-throttled — a 5th retry would mean either (a) a much wider schedule (40-60s cumulative, risking Vercel 60s maxDuration), or (b) a different unblock path entirely. Iter 151 picks (b). The infrastructure was already half-built: FREE_PNL=1 env flag (iter 105) reroutes getTaxReportRange() to getTaxReportRangeFree(), which reconstructs the same row shape from /api/account/history/v1 + /api/transfer/v1 — both available on the free Taostats tier, both rate-limit-friendlier on Vercel-egress (iter 150 confirmed the Mum wallets returned `delegation_cleared, tax/v1 still 429` — i.e. history/v1 was succeeding on the same Vercel-egress IP at the same moment tax/v1 was throwing 429). Iter 105 probe proved the reconstruction matches paid net_profit to the rao on 30d windows. Iter 151 ships a minimal wrap: getTaxReportRange now try/catches the paid taoGet, and on throw falls back to getTaxReportRangeFree (unless FREE_PNL_FALLBACK=0, the diagnostic escape hatch). The underlying paid-path error is console.warn-logged before fallback so Vercel runtime logs still surface the root cause for ongoing diagnosis — downstream callers (pnlGroundTruth, taxYearSection) just see a successful row set with no shape difference. The shape consistency is what makes this safe: iter 105 probe confirmed snapshot rows (rootOnly reconstruction) + transfer_in/transfer_out rows match the paid output to the rao, and pnlGroundTruth\'s loop logic (lib/report.js:204-242) consumes only transaction_type + credit_amount/debit_amount/total_balance, none of which differ between the two paths. Trade-off honest: when paid tax/v1 throws, free-path reconstruction adds ~3-5s of latency vs the cached paid path (the free path makes 2-4 history/v1 pages + 1 transfer/v1 page, ~5-8s on Vercel). But the alternative is the lying reason:"tax_fetch_failed" verdict iter 150 confirmed on 3 wallets. iter 151 trades ~5s of additional latency for a real iter 142 verdict on every wallet that\'s currently broken. Pre-commit smoke target: Mum_smf 5FzK9siZvs7TdFWbGHVFBQQSyiFriQ2yPvEhhA8Qf1JcQzmm — the simplest of the 3 tax_fetch_failed wallets, expected post-deploy: 200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and a sheet-parity verdict. IDEAL outcome = iter 142 verify lands on the first Mum wallet, completing 3-of-7 → 4-of-7 (or more if the free-path fallback also handles Mum_root + Mum_mantat in the same deploy). Mantat + Mum_subnets remain blocked on /api/delegation/v1 + /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 429s, which is an orthogonal fanout-burst problem queued for iter 152. Non-regressive: every existing caller of getTaxReportRange transparent — happy-path returns same shape, error path now returns valid data instead of throwing, FREE_PNL=1 mode unchanged (still skips paid entirely). FREE_PNL_FALLBACK=0 env escape hatch lets Jai disable the auto-fallback if he needs to expose raw paid throws for diagnostic work (e.g. confirming iter 149\'s backoff actually fired by inspecting the underlying exception). KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — reliability/recovery fix, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
