    title: 'pnlGroundTruth now distinguishes "tax_fetch_failed" (transient Vercel→Taostats 429 or timeout) from "no_tax_data" (Taostats genuinely empty) so iter 142\'s sheet-parity verdict no longer silently lies on 6 of Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys — the retroactive verify sweep on 2026-06-16 returned reason:"no_tax_data" from Vercel while direct VPS curl against /api/accounting/tax/v1 returned 312 rows (Subnets) and 230 rows (Mum_subnets), proving the .catch wrappers at lib/report.js:172 AND lib/report.js:2251 were both swallowing rate-limit errors as empty arrays',
    body:
      'Iter 147. Correctness fix uncovered during the retroactive iter 142 verify sweep — the headline finding of this iter is the root-cause diagnosis, not the code change. Setup: iter 146 unblocked the retroactive verify (server-side price cache makes multi-wallet sweeps tolerant of Vercel-egress stalls on /price/latest), so iter 147 ran the queued sweep against Jai\'s remaining 6 pinned coldkeys (Subnets, Mantat, Mum_root, Mum_smf, Mum_subnets, Mum_mantat) spaced 15s apart against tao-wallet-report.vercel.app/api/report?skipCache=1. Result: 4 of 6 returned 500 with Taostats 429 from /api/delegation/v1 or /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 (separate Vercel-egress throttle problem, queued for iter 148+); 2 of 6 (Subnets + Mum_subnets) returned 200 but with pnlGroundTruth = { available: false, reason: "no_tax_data" }. Direct VPS-side probe of /api/accounting/tax/v1 with token=TAO + date_start/date_end on the FY25-26 window returned 312 tax rows for Subnets and 230 for Mum_subnets — the data is plainly there. So the report\'s "no_tax_data" reason was a lie generated by the .catch(() => []) wrapper around getTaxReportRange at lib/report.js:2251 (the pre-fetch loop that powers both pnlGroundTruth and taxYearSection) — when Taostats rate-limited the Vercel call, the catch silently degraded the failure to an empty array, which pnlGroundTruth then re-interpreted as "wallet has no transactions in this FY." Same shape existed at lib/report.js:172 for the non-prefetched call path. This is THE reason iter 142\'s pnlFormulaParity verdict only ever appeared on Jai\'s primary Root coldkey (5Cnz1juP…) — Root happened to be the one wallet whose tax/v1 fetch consistently succeeded on Vercel because it sits earlier in the FY data range or trips fewer 429 buckets; every other wallet trips the swallow-and-mask. iter 147 ships two changes: (1) pnlGroundTruth signature gains rowsFetchError, the call site at lib/report.js:2251 captures errors per-FY into fyRowsErrorBySy + passes the current-FY error through as trailingRowsError. The non-prefetched code path inside pnlGroundTruth captures its own getTaxReport error directly. (2) The available:false return shape adds a new reason value "tax_fetch_failed" (distinct from "no_tax_data" and "no_balance") + an optional error field naming the underlying exception string. The UI consumers (app/_components/Report.jsx line 453, app/report/[coldkey]/page.jsx line 35, app/page.jsx line 118, app/report/[coldkey]/opengraph-image.jsx line 35, app/api/cron/weekly-emails/route.js line 65, lib/report-email.js line 103, lib/ai-insights.js line 75 + 719) all gate downstream rendering on gt.available, so a new reason string is purely informational — no UI regression risk, no consumer surprises. Bonus discovery resolved: iter 146 flagged "priceTao: None" as a surprise on Jai\'s primary response. The actual field is taoPriceUsd (number, top-level) — there is no priceTao key in the response shape. iter 146\'s extraction script was looking under the wrong key path. Noting it here so the field name is durable. Implication for iter 142 verify going forward: once iter 147 lands, a retroactive sweep that hits Vercel-egress 429s on tax/v1 will at least surface reason:"tax_fetch_failed" with the underlying error string instead of silently masquerading as a structural "this wallet has no tax data" — and a follow-up iter can decide whether to retry with backoff (iter 148?) or banner the failure to §0 alongside the queued "Taostats degraded" banner work. Trade-off: zero. This is a strictly more honest data shape — old behavior was "lie about why the verdict is missing", new behavior is "name the cause of the missing verdict." Non-regressive: no existing consumer parses the reason field beyond the available boolean gate, so adding a new reason is invisible to all callers. Pre-commit smoke logic verified inline (4 paths: success → unchanged, tax fetch error → tax_fetch_failed with error, empty rows + no error → no_tax_data, balance fetch failed → no_balance). KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — diagnostic precision, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). Iter 148 candidates: (a) tax/v1 429 retry-with-backoff on Vercel-egress (separate problem from /price/latest stall — different endpoint, different throttle bucket, different fix), (b) "Taostats degraded" §0 banner now wired to the new tax_fetch_failed signal (iter 147 gives the banner cleaner upstream evidence than iter 145\'s timeout-detection), (c) iter 142 parity verdict chip in §2 PnL UI block (UI-only, no API dep — could ship in parallel), (d) once 148a lands, complete the retroactive iter 142 verify sweep on the 4 wallets still blocked by 429s. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
