    date: '2026-06-15',
    tag: 'UX',
    title: 'Saved Wallets now first-class — labels, cached PnL snapshot on-device, big tappable cards above the search; "+ Add wallet" lets you stash a coldkey by name before ever running a report. Re-opening the homepage hydrates balance + PnL from localStorage instantly; no API call, no spinner, no Vercel cold-start wait',
    body:
      'Iter 141. Jai redirect on 2026-06-15 — top-of-stack priorities became (a) on-device wallet save UX (named, persistent, instant), (b) PnL parity with his Drive sheets (Bittensor Transactions + Bittensor portfolio tracker), and (c) load quicker. This iter ships (a) and (c) and lays the carry-state foundation that (b) will plug into next. Three changes ship: (1) app/_components/PinnedColdkeys.jsx — schema grows from `{coldkey, note, pinnedAt}` to `{coldkey, label, note, pinnedAt, lastBalanceTao, lastProfitTao, lastReturnPct, lastSnapshotAt}` with a normaliseEntry() loader so old pins keep working (note still renders as the display name if no label is set). New exports updateLabel() + updatePinSnapshot() — the latter writes balance + profit + return % into the pin without resaving if nothing changed (avoids cross-tab event spam). The component itself stops being a chip row and becomes a CSS-grid of saved-wallet cards: big label, short SS58 in mono, then the cached balance τ and PnL τ + return % with pos/neg colour, plus a "snapshot Xm ago" age marker. Empty-state copy explains the value prop. A "+ Add wallet" button at the top opens two prompts (coldkey + label) and validates SS58 client-side, so Jai can save his 7 named wallets in 30 seconds without first building a report for each. Rename and remove buttons sit in a footer strip per card. (2) app/_components/PinButton.jsx — accepts an optional `pnl` prop (passed as report.pnlGroundTruth from both the homepage and the /report/[coldkey] permalink), snapshots currentPortfolioTao/profitTao/returnPct when pinning, and a useEffect re-syncs the snapshot whenever a fresh report renders for an already-saved wallet, so the saved-wallet card on the next visit reflects the most recent build. Button text now reads "Save wallet" / "Saved" (lighter language than "Pin this report" — matches the saved-wallets framing). (3) app/page.jsx + app/report/[coldkey]/page.jsx — wire pnl prop into PinButton; on the homepage the SavedWallets section moves ABOVE the search form so it is the first thing a returning user sees. (4) app/api/report/route.js + app/report/[coldkey]/page.jsx — maxDuration bumped 30s → 60s. Earlier today both Subnets and Root coldkeys timed out at exactly 30.5s with FUNCTION_INVOCATION_TIMEOUT on cold cache; 60s is the Vercel Pro Node ceiling and gives genuine headroom for a full first build. (5) app/globals.css — new .saved-wallets / .saved-wallet-card / .saved-wallet-snap / .saved-wallet-pnl rule block, responsive grid (auto-fill minmax 220px), hover lift, action footer with split rename/remove buttons. Why this matters on the load-quicker axis: even with the maxDuration bump, the first build of an uncached coldkey still takes 10–25 seconds — that wait is unavoidable on cold cache. But for the 99% case of a returning user opening the homepage, the saved-wallet cards now render their last-known balance + PnL from localStorage on first paint with zero network round-trip. The card is also a Link to /report/[coldkey] which uses the SSR cache (5min TTL), so tapping into a fresh report is the second-fastest path. PnL parity with Drive sheets (priority b) needs a separate research iter: the sheet uses `current_balance + transfer_out − transfer_in − starting_balance` for accumulation wallets (Subnets / Mantat / Mum_subnets / Mum_mantat) but `current_balance − (transfer_in − transfer_out)` for harvest wallets (Root / Mum_root / Mum_smf) — the app today applies the accumulation formula across the board, which is why headline numbers can drift on the harvest wallets. Iter 142 candidate: pull a coldkey-type classifier (heuristic on transfer cadence + dominant transaction type) and branch the pnlGroundTruth formula to match the sheet exactly. Smoke-tested locally: old pins load through normaliseEntry without losing the note, addPin() now accepts either a string (legacy) or an opts object, updatePinSnapshot guards against null/NaN, no-op when values unchanged. KB layer-stack and KB→§0 bridge counts unchanged — this iter is on the wallet-save UX axis, not the AI verdict axis.',
