    tag: 'ai',
    title: '§2 PNL now carries an alpha-weighted multi-window price-momentum quartet (1h × 1d × 7d × 30d) beside the existing trio, with a 6-state directional verdict (sustained_uptrend / sustained_downtrend / recent_reversal_to_up / recent_reversal_to_down / chop / flat) derived from the 1d/7d/30d trio so §0 can read today\'s slice against the 30d arc — pairs with iter 137\'s multi-window staking-flow durability on the BEHAVIOURAL axis, this one closes the PRICE axis, and rides as the 8th deterministic verdict row in the §0 error card when Pollinations is down',
    body:
      'Iter 140. Priority 3 longer-window stats — second multi-window depth slice after iter 137\'s staking-flow durability tree. Symmetric structure: where iter 137 reads the BEHAVIOURAL axis (transfer flow direction across 30d / 90d / 180d / 365d), iter 140 reads the PRICE axis (alpha-weighted portfolio % across 1h / 1d / 7d / 30d). The 1d delta has shipped since the §2 PNL block first existed — same with 7d and 30d — but they\'ve always been three independent numbers without a directional read. Iter 140 adds the 1h slice to complete the quartet, recomposes the four windows as a depth ladder, and runs a 6-state classifier so §0 can distinguish "portfolio down 2% today after being down 12% over 30d" (sustained_downtrend, durable headwind) from "portfolio down 2% today after being UP 12% over 30d" (recent_reversal_to_down, watch for confirmation) — which the existing trio surfaced as the same three signed numbers without naming the arc. Three changes ship: (1) lib/report.js §1 portfolio adds `pct1h: sn.price_1h_pct_change` to per-position rows. tao.app screener already returns price_1h_pct_change on every subnet — confirmed live against api.tao.app/api/beta/subnet_screener with the standard plan key, returned -0.0008% on netuid 1 at probe time (1h moves are intra-hour noisy but the field is populated). (2) lib/report.js §2 PNL adds change1hTao = periodChange(\'pct1h\') beside the existing change24h/7d/30d, then builds a new multiWindowPriceMomentum block: { available, windows:[{label:1h,changeTao,changeUsd,pctPortfolio}, … 1d, 7d, 30d], verdict, verdictReason, flatThresholdPct:0.5 }. Verdict logic — the directional read uses only the 1d/7d/30d trio because 1h pct changes are inherently noisy intra-hour (the probe returned 0.0008%, well inside any reasonable threshold). Threshold 0.5% of portfolio per window decides flat-vs-directional; below threshold is sign=0. Six verdict states: all-three-positive → sustained_uptrend, all-three-negative → sustained_downtrend, all-three-zero → flat, 30d/7d negative + 1d positive → recent_reversal_to_up, 30d/7d positive + 1d negative → recent_reversal_to_down, otherwise → chop. 1h IS surfaced in the windows array as the leading-edge detail (so the AI can mention "down 5% today, still ticking lower in the last hour" or "down 5% today but stabilising in the last hour" if it wants) but never flips the verdict. Verdict reason string includes the three trio pcts verbatim so the LLM and the §0 fallback row both render numbers, not just labels. Edge cases: currentTao≤0 → available:false / reason:empty_portfolio; null pct1h on a position → periodChange treats null as no contribution (existing behaviour for the 1d/7d/30d trio), 1h window pctPortfolio reads 0, verdict still computes correctly from 1d/7d/30d. (3) lib/ai-insights.js buildVerdictFallback adds an 8th row (between stakingFlowDurability at #7 and emissionAlignment at #9) gated on report.pnl?.multiWindowPriceMomentum?.available && verdict — key "priceMomentum", label "Price momentum (1h / 1d / 7d / 30d)", verdict from the classifier, interpretation = verdictReason. Now §0 carries TWO multi-window depth signals through the fallback: BEHAVIOURAL (stakingFlowDurability, iter 137 + iter 139 dormant state) and PRICE (priceMomentum, iter 140) — symmetric depth coverage on the two axes the report can actually measure. Also extends lib/ai-insights.js buildUserPrompt §2 PNL section: the existing "24h · 7d · 30d" line now reads "1h · 24h · 7d · 30d" and a new "Multi-window momentum: <verdict> — 1h:X% · 1d:X% · 7d:X% · 30d:X%. <verdictReason>" line follows, so gpt-oss-20b sees the named arc directly in the prompt and can use it in What Changed to frame the 1d slice against the 30d trend. Pre-commit smoke 18/18 PASS on isolated cases: all six verdicts fire on canonical pct vectors, empty portfolio → unavailable / reason:empty_portfolio, null pct1h still produces correct trio-based verdict with 1h window pctPortfolio:0, buildVerdictFallback emits the priceMomentum row when available and skips when unavailable, window order is 1h,1d,7d,30d (regression guard against label reorder), verdict reason text mentions both 1d and 30d pcts. KB layer-stack climbs from THIRTEEN to FOURTEEN with the price-momentum classifier (THIRTEEN was iter 137 durability tree + iter 139 dormant state on the behavioural axis; iter 140 adds the price-axis classifier). KB→§0 bridges climb from SIX to SEVEN (117/118, 121/122, 123/124, 125/126/127, 128/129, 131/132, NEW pnl 117/140). The PRICE-axis depth ladder is now complete from the 1h leading edge to the 30d arc; further iters on this axis would have to either expand WIDTH (90d/180d/365d price momentum — but Taostats screener doesn\'t expose those windows, would need an external API) or move to PER-SUBNET momentum verdicts (price-axis equivalent of iter 137\'s per-validator durability). Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch + draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff (last updated_at 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z, ~28hr hold by 10:05Z). Natural iter 141 candidates: (a) embed verdictFallback in the SSR page payload to cover the Vercel maxDuration 504 timeout gap iter 136 left open (route catch can\'t fire when runtime is killed before /api/insights returns — observed at iter 137 verify, iter 139 verify); (b) cache-warm yield calls serially to fix cold-start 429 burst on first coldkey-per-instance (Taostats /api/price/latest/v1 throttle observed at iter 138 verify); (c) PER-SUBNET price-momentum verdicts so What Changed can name the specific subnet driving the portfolio-level arc — adjacent extension of this iter rather than a new axis; (d) embed multiWindowPriceMomentum in the §2 PNL UI surface (currently emits the verdict but the component side hasn\'t rendered it — would surface the durability chip beside the existing change pills).',
