    title: 'Multi-window staking-flow durability layer now names the dormant-wallet state explicitly — when a coldkey has zero transfer_in/transfer_out events across the trailing 365d window (pure root-staked harvest behaviour like Jai\'s primary 5Cnz1juP…), multiWindowDurabilityVerdict emits a new `dormant_harvest_only` verdict rather than returning available:false, so the §0 staking-flow block surfaces a meaningful read ("validator selection and root staking ARE the strategy") instead of soft-omitting. Closes the iter 138 verify gap where the structural shape fix landed but the data input was empty on Jai\'s primary, leaving §0 with no behavioural-flow signal at all even though the absence of flow IS itself the signal',
    body:
      'Iter 139. Fix-forward on iter 138 verify gap. Iter 138 confirmed the structural shape fix landed (multiWindowNetFlow + multiWindowDurability now attach to stakingFlowVerdict regardless of sfVerdict.available) but the live curl on Jai\'s primary 5Cnz1juP… revealed mwnf.available:False / mwnf.reason:"no_rows" — the combined FY24-25 + FY25-26 tax-row fetch (23 months of coverage) returned ZERO transfer events. Initial pivot considered extending the FY fetch window backwards (FY23-24, FY22-23) but ruled out: the multi-window read is a 365d-rolling window from now, so going further back than ~Jul 2024 adds rows that fall outside the window cutoff and won\'t contribute. The wallet is truly root-staked harvest-only since well over a year ago — no in/out capital movement, validator selection IS the strategy. The correct read is to name THAT state explicitly rather than treat it as missing data. Three changes ship: (1) lib/report.js multiWindowDurabilityVerdict gains an escape-hatch branch at the top: when mwnf is provided but mwnf.available is false AND mwnf.reason is one of `no_rows` (rows array was empty — wallet has no tax events at all in the 2-FY combined window) or `no_transfers_in_365d` (wallet has tax events but none of them are transfer_in/transfer_out — pure stake_added/stake_removed/etc.), return { available:true, verdict:"dormant_harvest_only", verdictReason:"wallet has zero transfer_in/transfer_out events across the trailing 365d — pure root-staking harvest behaviour; validator selection and root staking ARE the strategy, behavioural capital-flow signals do not apply", points:null }. The points field stays null because there\'s no per-window numeric data to render — the dormant verdict carries semantic content but no quantitative payload. All other branches (sustained_accumulation, sustained_distribution, recent_reversal_*, one_off_spike, fading_flow, flat, mixed) are unchanged. The defensive `if (!mwnf?.available || !Array.isArray(mwnf.points))` guard further down still short-circuits any other unavailable path to { available:false }, so wallets with rows but missing window buckets still soft-omit correctly. (2) lib/ai-insights.js multi-window block gets a new branch: the primary `if (mwnf?.available && mwDur?.available)` block renders the standard numeric net-flow line + durability verdict; a new `else if (mwDur?.available && mwDur.verdict === "dormant_harvest_only")` branch renders WITHOUT the numeric net-flow line (would only be ±0τ noise — the LLM might hallucinate flow values if given window points) and closes with a sharply-worded instruction telling gpt-oss-20b: "Do NOT narrate this as no signal or insufficient data — the absence of behavioural-flow activity IS the read. Frame the Summary and Recommendations around validator/subnet selection and root-stake APY as the load-bearing levers; behavioural rebalancing is not a tool this wallet is using and not something to recommend as a missing dimension." This is the load-bearing piece — without it, gpt-oss-20b would see "Durability verdict: dormant_harvest_only" and likely write "no flow data" or "wallet is inactive" in Summary, missing that the verdict itself is the positive signal. (3) buildVerdictFallback at lib/ai-insights.js line 657 is structurally unchanged — it already gates the stakingFlowDurability row on `mwDur?.available && mwDur.verdict`, so the new dormant verdict automatically rides through into the §0 error-card fallback list as "Staking flow durability: `dormant_harvest_only` — wallet has zero transfer_in/transfer_out events across the trailing 365d — pure root-staking harvest behaviour; validator selection and root staking ARE the strategy, behavioural capital-flow signals do not apply" when Pollinations is down. Pre-commit smoke 12/12 PASS on isolated cases: (a) empty rows → mwnf.available=false / reason=no_rows → mwDur dormant_harvest_only available + points:null, (b) stake-only rows (no transfers) → mwnf.reason=no_transfers_in_365d → mwDur dormant_harvest_only, (c) real transfer rows in all 4 windows → mwDur sustained_accumulation (NOT dormant — confirms the new branch doesn\'t leak into the data-rich path), (d) buildVerdictFallback emits stakingFlowDurability row with dormant verdict + full verdictReason text, (e) null mwnf → mwDur unavailable (defensive), (f) malformed mwnf with available:true but no points array → mwDur unavailable (defensive shortcut still fires). KB layer-stack stays THIRTEEN — iter 139 adds a new verdict state to the existing durability classifier rather than a new KB axis. KB→§0 bridges stay SIX (117/118, 121/122, 123/124, 125/126/127, 128/129, 131/132). Coverage extension on the iter 137 durability tree: 7 → 8 verdict states (added dormant_harvest_only). The data-input gap on FY-quiet pure-harvest wallets that iter 138 verify exposed is now closed at the verdict layer rather than the data layer — appropriate because the data layer was correctly reporting "no flow" and the issue was that "no flow" deserved an explicit name. Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch + draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff (last updated_at 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z, ~26+hr hold). Natural iter 140 candidates: (a) §3 quartet portfolio roll-up (alpha-weighted 1h × 1d × 7d × 30d quartet beside the existing 1d-delta block as portfolio-wide depth signal — Priority 3 longer-window stats, deepest remaining axis now that the durability tree covers all canonical wallet states from sustained_accumulation through dormant_harvest_only); (b) embed verdictFallback in the SSR page payload to cover the Vercel maxDuration 504 timeout gap iter 136 left open (route catch can\'t fire when runtime is killed before /api/insights returns); (c) cache-warm yield endpoint serially to fix cold-start 429 burst on first coldkey-per-instance.',
