    tag: 'ai',
    title: 'Iter 137 multi-window staking-flow data now surfaces independently of the single-window verdict — closes the gating gap exposed on Jai\'s primary 5Cnz1juP… coldkey where pnlGroundTruth returns available:false (no transfers inside the FY-bound window) so stakingFlowVerdict.available was false and the iter 137 attachment was silently dropped, even though the 365d raw tax-row scan held years of transfer history. lib/report.js now attaches multiWindowNetFlow + multiWindowDurability to stakingFlowVerdict unconditionally; lib/ai-insights.js lifts the multi-window block out of the sf.available gate and emits it as its own ## Multi-window staking flow (computed) heading. buildVerdictFallback unchanged but the underlying availability shift means the §0 error card now surfaces "Staking flow durability" for wallets that previously rendered no flow signal at all',
    body:
      'Iter 138. Fix-forward on iter 137 verify gap. The iter 137 verify chain confirmed deploy READY + changelog top H2 correct + monkey-patched §0 error card renders the 7-row verdict fallback including the new "Staking flow durability" row — but the live /api/report ride-along on Jai\'s primary 5Cnz1juP… coldkey exposed that stakingFlowVerdict was `{available:false}` and the iter 137 multi-window enrichment was nowhere to be found in the report payload. Root cause traced through lib/report.js line 2367 (pre-fix): `if (sfVerdict?.available) { sfVerdict.multiWindowNetFlow = mwnf; sfVerdict.multiWindowDurability = mwDurability; }` — the attachment was gated on the SAME availability flag that the single-window staking-flow verdict uses. Single-window stakingFlowVerdict reads gt.transferInTao/transferOutTao/transferCount which are sourced from pnlGroundTruth, which is FY-windowed (current Australian FY = 2025-07-01 onwards). Jai\'s primary 5Cnz1juP… has zero transfer events inside the current FY window — root-staked, harvest-only, no in/out flows — so gt.available is false, sfVerdict.available is false, and iter 137\'s enrichment never lands on the response. But multiWindowNetFlow({ rows: allTaxRows }) operates on the COMBINED prior + current FY raw tax rows (built at line 2357-2361 from fyRowsBySy across both years) and walks them with a rolling 365d window — that data is rich for Jai\'s primary (years of historical transfers in the prior-FY bucket). The single-window staking-flow read and the multi-window durability read are independent signals at the data layer; iter 137 conflated them at the attachment layer. Three changes ship: (1) lib/report.js — replace `if (sfVerdict?.available)` with `if (sfVerdict)`. The inner availability flags on mwnf (gated on has365Flow, i.e. ≥1 transfer in the 365d rolling window) and mwDurability (gated on mwnf.available + four window buckets present) still gate downstream rendering, so a brand-new coldkey with truly no transfer history still rides cleanly through — but a wallet like Jai\'s primary with quiet recent activity and rich long-arc history now gets the multi-window enrichment attached to its `{available:false}` sfVerdict object. The shape downstream consumers read becomes `stakingFlowVerdict: { available:false, multiWindowNetFlow:{available:true,points:[...]}, multiWindowDurability:{available:true,verdict:"...",verdictReason:"..."} }` for these wallets, which is the correct independent-signal shape. (2) lib/ai-insights.js — pull the multi-window block (formerly nested inside `if (sf?.available)` at lines 377-386) out into its own top-level `if (mwnf?.available && mwDur?.available)` block with a new `## Multi-window staking flow (computed)` heading. The block emits a `Net flow by window: 30d ±Xτ (N txns) · 90d … · 180d … · 365d …` numeric line + `Durability verdict: <verdict> — <verdictReason>` classification line, then branches the closing instruction by whether single-window sf is also available: when sf is unavailable, the closing line explicitly tells the LLM "the multi-window durability read above is the ONLY behavioural-flow signal for this wallet — narrate it explicitly in Summary or Recommendations; do not fall back to no flow data when the long-arc read has material content" (forces gpt-oss-20b to engage rather than soft-omit on the missing single-window pair); when sf IS available, the closing line preserves the iter 137 long-arc-vs-recent-slice contrast instruction. (3) buildVerdictFallback at lib/ai-insights.js line 657 is structurally unchanged — it already gates the stakingFlowDurability row on `report.stakingFlowVerdict?.multiWindowDurability?.available` without checking sfVerdict.available, so the helper just starts emitting the 7th row on wallets where the attachment now lands. The closing instruction shift in the user prompt (#2) is the load-bearing piece — without it, gpt-oss-20b would see the §0 prompt for Jai\'s primary with NO staking-flow section heading at all (sf unavailable, multi-window block was hidden inside sf gate) and write "no flow data" in Summary; with this iter, the wallet gets the multi-window heading as its only staking-flow signal and the LLM is instructed to engage. Smoke-tested 10 cases in isolation pre-commit (multi-window attachment with rows produces 4 windows, attaches to {available:false} sfVerdict, buildVerdictFallback emits stakingFlowDurability when sf.available=false but mwDur.available=true and does NOT emit the single-window stakingFlow row, empty rows → mwnf.available=false → mwDur.available=false → no stakingFlowDurability row → backwards-compat preserved) — all PASS. KB layer-stack stays THIRTEEN (iter 137 added the durability layer; iter 138 fixes its visibility on FY-quiet wallets without adding a new KB axis). Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch + draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff (last updated_at 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z, ~25.3hr hold by 09:15Z). Natural iter 139 candidates: (a) §3 quartet portfolio roll-up (alpha-weighted 1h × 1d × 7d × 30d quartet beside the existing 1d-delta block as portfolio-wide depth signal — Priority 3 longer-window stats, deepest remaining axis now that iter 137 enrichment is universally visible); (b) embed verdictFallback in the SSR page payload to cover the Vercel maxDuration 504 timeout gap iter 136 left open (catch-block can\'t fire when the runtime is killed before /api/insights completes — observed in iter 137 verify curl returning HTML 504 not JSON); (c) cache-warm yield endpoint serially to fix cold-start 429 burst (observed at iter 137 verify nav — Taostats /api/price/latest/v1 returned 429 on first SSR call after long idle).',
