    body:
      'Iter 137. Priority 3 multi-window net-flow comparison ships — first depth slice on staking flow since iter 123, addresses Jai\'s iter-47 priority 3 ("more detailed report") on the deepest remaining axis after the iter 134/135/136 §0 error-surface trilogy structurally closed. Four changes ship together: (1) lib/report.js new exported multiWindowNetFlow({ rows, now }) helper walks tax rows once and tallies transfer_in / transfer_out for trailing 30d / 90d / 180d / 365d windows. Returns an array of { windowDays, netTao, transferInTao, transferOutTao, transferCount } points + an availability gate that returns false when even the 365d window saw zero transfer events (rather than emitting four ±0τ rows that the AI would misread as "sustained flat" — explicit "no flow data" signals soft-omit). Zero extra API cost — runs on tax rows already fetched for pnlGroundTruth + taxYearSection (combined prior + current FY rows so the 365d window has real coverage in the first half of any new FY, not just current-FY-only that would underfill July through January). (2) lib/report.js new exported multiWindowDurabilityVerdict({ mwnf, book }) classifier reads the four window net-flow tallies as a sequence and returns a single-word verdict + reason. Eight-state tree: sustained_accumulation (all four windows net positive AND year-net materially nonzero), sustained_distribution (all four windows net negative AND year-net materially nonzero), recent_reversal_to_accumulation (30d positive but 365d negative with both materially nonzero — name the reversal), recent_reversal_to_distribution (30d negative but 365d positive with both materially nonzero — name the reversal), one_off_spike (≥80% of 365d gross flow concentrated in the last 30d — single recent event dominates the year), fading_flow (365d had material flow but 30d went quiet — flow regime has paused), flat (all four windows within ±1τ — no behavioural signal worth narrating), mixed (no monotonic arc — read each window separately). Materiality floor uses max(1τ, 0.5% of currentPortfolioTao) so a 5τ flow on a 500τ book reads as immaterial without forcing the same threshold on a 10τ book. (3) lib/report.js buildReport wires it through — calls multiWindowNetFlow with combined prior + current FY rows, then multiWindowDurabilityVerdict, and attaches the result to stakingFlowVerdict.multiWindowNetFlow + stakingFlowVerdict.multiWindowDurability when both available (gated on sfVerdict.available so root-only books with no staking-flow data don\'t carry orphan multi-window data). (4) lib/ai-insights.js §0 staking-flow block surfaces the new fields: "Multi-window net flow: 30d +Xτ (N txns) · 90d ... · 180d ... · 365d ..." numeric line, "Durability: <verdict> — <verdictReason>" classification line, and a closing instruction that the durability frame is the LONG ARC and the existing single-window verdict is the RECENT slice — narrate as "[durability]; this month [single-window read]" not as two independent signals. Also extends lib/ai-insights.js buildVerdictFallback() so the durability verdict rides as a separate fallback row in the §0 error card (gated on stakingFlowVerdict.multiWindowDurability.available), surfacing the long-arc read alongside the single-window staking-flow verdict when Pollinations is down. (5) lib/bittensor-kb.js STAKING_FLOW_HEURISTICS extended with two new bullets describing the multi-window durability layer: maps each of the 8 verdicts to a single-line narration rule (sustained_accumulation → "year-long position build, recent continues the arc"; recent_reversal_to_accumulation → "flipped from year-long distribution to recent accumulation — name the reversal"; etc.) and codifies that the durability frame supersedes the single-window verdict for behaviour INTERPRETATION but not for MAGNITUDE — the existing 2% / 15% of-book gates still decide whether the recent slice reads as material or noise. KB→§0 cadence: closes the seventh bridge pair (117/118, 121/122, 123/124, 125/126/127, 128/129, 131/132, NEW 123/137) — same source verdict family as iter 123 (staking flow), now with a durability layer on top. KB layer-stack climbs from TWELVE to THIRTEEN with the new durability bullets. Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch + draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff (last updated_at 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z, ~26hr hold by 09:05Z). Natural iter 138 candidates: (a) §3 quartet portfolio roll-up (alpha-weighted 1h × 1d × 7d × 30d quartet beside the existing 1d-delta block — Priority 3 longer-window stats, second-deepest depth-debt after this); (b) embed verdictFallback in the SSR page payload to cover the Vercel maxDuration 504 timeout gap iter 136 left open (catch-block can\'t fire when the runtime is killed); (c) cache-warming yield calls serially to fix cold-start 429 burst on first coldkey-per-instance (5 consecutive 429s on mantat verify path before iter 134 chase).',
