    title: '§0 Drawdown verdict now reads the underwater-stretch distribution from iter 131 — sixth KB→§0 deterministic handoff bridge (117/118, 121/122, 123/124, 125/126/127, 128/129, 131/132). Two new verdict labels (beyond_historical_tail, within_typical_stretch) gate ahead of the absolute-threshold tree when the distribution carries ≥2 stretches, so the model reads "47d underwater past p90 of 50d → durability concern, not yield response" or "15d underwater at or below p50 of 25d → matches normal book behaviour, monitor not flag" instead of treating depth and duration in a vacuum',
