      'Iter 132. Closes the iter 131 → 132 KB→§0 handoff cadence — same pattern as 117 KB → 118 §0 PnL decomp, 121 KB → 122 §0 drawdown verdict, 123 KB → 124 §0 staking-flow, 125 KB → 126/127 §0 emission alignment, 128 KB → 129 §0 yield quartet. Two changes ship together: (1) lib/report.js drawdownVerdict() reads ddDurationP50, ddDurationP90, ddDurationMax and underwaterRunCount off the dd block (added iter 131) and gates two new verdict labels ahead of the existing absolute-threshold tree when underwaterRunCount ≥ 2 (distribution is only meaningful with at least two stretches — a single underwater run can\'t shape p50 vs p90, every percentile equals the same value). New label beyond_historical_tail fires when currentlyUnderwater AND daysUnderwater > ddDurationP90 — escalates the verdict above flag_worthy even if the 30%-depth gate hasn\'t tripped, because the current stretch is past the slow-recovery tail of the historical distribution (durability-signal escalation: depth alone may not be flag-worthy but duration alone now is, out-of-sample). New label within_typical_stretch fires when currentlyUnderwater AND daysUnderwater ≤ ddDurationP50 AND currentDrawdownPct ≤ 30% — down-weights what would otherwise classify as recent_deep_dip / shallow_but_extended / material_dip, because the current stretch is at or below the median historical underwater run and the duration matches normal book behaviour rather than a structural event. The 30%-depth gate stays load-bearing inside within_typical_stretch (a deep dip is a deep dip regardless of duration matching the median), and flag_worthy still wins outright on its dual gate (>30% depth AND >30d duration) — within_typical_stretch only applies in the gap zone where shallow duration would have over-fired the absolute tree. The existing at_peak / resilient_absorb / recovered / recent_noise paths are unchanged because the non-underwater branches don\'t intersect the distribution. (2) lib/ai-insights.js §0 drawdown-verdict block adds a numeric Underwater-stretch distribution (365d) line reading "p50 Xd · p90 Yd · max Zd across N stretches" right after the existing max/current/peak/uwStr line, mirroring the iter 118 PnL-decomp ratios pattern and iter 127 emission-alignment magnitudes pattern — the model reads the distribution numbers alongside the verdict so it can paraphrase the comparison in Summary without re-deriving it from the dd panel above. Conditional follow-on lines on the two new verdicts explain the routing decision (beyond_historical_tail → durability concern, route to concentration / sizing, not yield; within_typical_stretch → suppress alarm framing even on a deep-looking dip). Gating on dv.distAvailable (set on the verdict object whenever underwaterRunCount ≥ 2 with both percentiles present) so books with a single historical stretch render the existing four-field dd line without an empty distribution line. Smoke-tested all six verdict branches in isolation pre-commit (beyond_historical_tail correctly overrides flag_worthy depth gate; flag_worthy still wins when daysUnderwater ≤ p90; within_typical_stretch correctly down-weights material_dip; within_typical_stretch correctly blocked when curPct > 30% so depth keeps biting; distAvailable=false on single-stretch books falls back to the old tree; at_peak unchanged regardless of distribution). KB layer-stack stays TWELVE deep (no new KB axis), but the dd verdict tree climbs from 8 → 10 labels and the §0 hand-off now carries dip SHAPE not just dip depth — closes the depth-and-recency gap iter 131 opened on the user side. Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch + draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff (last updated_at 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z, ~19hr hold).',
