      'Iter 126. Priority 2 (AI KB deepening) slice — KB-first half of the iter 125 → iter 127 handoff pair, fourth KB→§0 bridge in the established cadence (117/118 PnL decomp, 121/122 drawdown, 123/124 staking-flow, 125/126/127 emission alignment — this slice deviates from the strict 2-step pattern only because iter 125 was a structural-section pre-compute first, not a KB layer). The portfolio.emissionAlignment block has been on report objects since iter 125 but the §0 KB had zero framework for reading it, so the model would either ignore the emission dimension entirely or anchor on the wrong signal (treat coveredEmissionPct as if it were highEmissionShare and conclude a long tail of small positions in big subnets is structurally aligned when the TAO is concentrated in starved ones). New EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS block in lib/bittensor-kb.js codifies eight read-rules: (1) emission_pct is the CANONICAL per-subnet network emission share that sums to 100 across the 128-subnet universe — not a proxy — and the 1.0% gate is one full point above the 1/128 ≈ 0.78% fair-share line; (2) four-state verdict ranking with structural-risk-first ordering — starved_subnet_heavy outranks partially_aligned because absent coverage is a fixable allocation choice while zero-emission-heavy is a structural earnings-power problem (emission is the input to yield, and there\'s nothing to distribute regardless of which hotkey you delegate to); (3) weightedEmissionPct bands — < 0.5% is the harvesting-from-dead-subnets red flag (the yield line will reflect this no matter how good the validator is), 0.5-1.0% workable, 1.0-2.0% aligned, > 2.0% concentrated in emission winners with the pair-read warning to cross-reference concentration; (4) highEmissionShare vs coveredEmissionPct distinction — a book can have high coveredEmissionPct via a long tail in big subnets but low highEmissionShare if the TAO is concentrated in starved ones, in which case the long tail is performative breadth; (5) zeroEmissionShare ≥ 50% structural-risk extreme — recovery is a thesis call (validator politics, governance, weight-vote outcomes) not a yield call, so SIZE DOWN until weights confirm rather than re-delegate; (6) mostOverweightLowEmission codified as the natural TRIM anchor when verdict is starved-leaning (the largest individual position carrying the most TAO with the weakest emission claim has the biggest structural-risk-trim impact per τ moved), with explicit framing "trim <subnet> from X% toward Y%" not generic "rebalance"; (7) RESPONSE-AXIS GUARD — emission alignment is a SUBNET SELECTION problem, not a validator selection problem, so the right responses are TRIM the starved overweight + REALLOCATE into emission-aligned Tier 1/Tier 2 subnets and explicitly NOT validator re-delegation (switching hotkeys on a zero-emission subnet just moves a zero around — same anti-misdiagnosis guard rail iter 116 added for concentration and iter 121 added for drawdown); (8) cross-reference VALIDATOR_HEURISTICS — a high APY snapshot on a zero-emission subnet is almost always a sampling artefact (single epoch with stray emission or yield calc from prior weights) so treat such APY numbers with skepticism in the recommendation pass; plus a no-data fallback for the { available: false, reason: \'no_emission_data\' } case (root-only books, screener field rename, transient API outage) — skip the read rather than guess. EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS appended to KB_TEXT after STAKING_FLOW_HEURISTICS so the model now sees: maturity → time-windows → validators → categories → PnL decomp → drawdown → staking flow → emission alignment. Inference cost on Pollinations is $0; ~250 extra prompt tokens. Iter 127 will operationalise this with an emissionAlignmentVerdict() helper or direct surfacing of the existing report.portfolio.emissionAlignment block into §0 with the structural-risk read-rule rendered as a closing instruction, mirroring the 117→118 / 121→122 / 123→124 KB→§0 pattern. Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch and draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff. AI KB layer-stack now ELEVEN deep.',
