      'Iter 125. Priority 3 structural-depth slice — broadens the deterministic surface beyond §0 by adding a new dimension to §1 portfolio that has not been measured anywhere in the report so far: subnet emission alignment. The screener has been returning emission_pct on every subnet for months (it sums to exactly 100 across the 128-subnet universe — it IS the canonical network emission share, not a proxy) but the report never surfaced it, so a wallet that\'s 80% concentrated in starved subnets (emission_pct == 0, validator weights routed entirely elsewhere this epoch) looked structurally identical to a wallet 80% concentrated in the top emission producers like Targon (2.7%) or Score (6.8%). New per-position emissionPct field on every entry in top10 and allPositions (null-safe Number coercion from sn.emission_pct). New portfolio.emissionAlignment block computed across positions with emission data: weightedEmissionPct = Σ (taoValue × emissionPct) / totalTao (the per-TAO average network emission share — high means your TAO is concentrated in subnets that capture network emission, low means your TAO sits where emission isn\'t flowing this epoch); highEmissionShare = % of book in subnets with emission_pct ≥ 1.0% (one full percentage point of network emission, materially above the 1/128 ≈ 0.78% fair share); zeroEmissionShare = % of book in subnets currently receiving zero network emission; coveredEmissionPct = sum of unique held subnets\' emission_pct (raw breadth, ignores weight — answers "what slice of the emission pie does your holdings list cover"); mostOverweightLowEmission = highest pctOfPortfolio among top10 positions with emission_pct < 1.0% (the structural-risk anchor when verdict is starved-leaning). Five-state verdict: aligned_with_emission (highEmissionShare ≥ 60%), partially_aligned (≥ 30%), starved_subnet_heavy (zeroEmissionShare ≥ 50%), mixed (otherwise), or { available: false, reason: \'no_emission_data\' } when the screener didn\'t return emission_pct on any held subnet (root-only books, screener field rename, API outage). UI render untouched this iter — keeps the diff tight; the field is purely additive to the portfolio shape so all existing consumers (Report.jsx top10 table, opengraph image, CSV export, report-email top5, alignment in §5 recs) keep working. This sets up the iter 126 KB→§0 handoff pair following the established 117/118, 121/122, 123/124 pattern: iter 126 will likely add EMISSION_ALIGNMENT_HEURISTICS to lib/bittensor-kb.js codifying how to read the weightedEmissionPct triple + the verdict + the mostOverweightLowEmission anchor, then iter 127 surfaces the verdict in §0 with a structural-risk read-rule ("the response axis is concentration/rebalancing, not validator-switching — emission-starved subnets won\'t pay yield no matter which hotkey you delegate to"). Non-blocking: paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch and draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff. AI KB layer-stack still at ten — this is a structural-section deepening, not a KB layer.',
