    title: 'AI KB: validator-selection heuristics added — when to act on the re-delegation opportunities iter 114 surfaces, in absolute τ/year terms not percentage-point deltas, with concentration-risk and alpha-pool-slippage gates',
    body:
      'Iter 116. Priority 2 slice — closes the loop on iter 114. Iter 114 shipped the DATA (top-5 re-delegation opportunities + portfolio-level optimised-case lift in the user prompt), but the KB had no FRAMEWORK for reasoning about it: the model would either recommend every switch above 5pp blindly, or dismiss them all as "marginal". New VALIDATOR_HEURISTICS block in lib/bittensor-kb.js codifies: (a) OTF is the network default — reliable, low/zero commission, but not always the highest yielder on a given subnet; (b) commercial validators (RoundTable21, TaoTemple, Yuma, FirstTensor, Polychain) compete on commission + uptime — named are generally safe, unknown 48-char hotkeys with no human name are higher risk; (c) re-delegation lift thresholds, per-position: < 0.05τ/year not worth it, 0.05-0.5τ/year "consider", > 0.5τ/year "recommend", > 2τ/year "act now"; (d) reason in absolute τ/year not percentage-point delta — a 5pp gap on a < 5τ position is structurally smaller than a 2pp gap on a 50τ position; (e) 1d APY snapshots are noisy at the validator level (single epoch can swing 30%+), prefer 7d/30d-smoothed; (f) re-delegation costs ~0.001τ in network fees but trades the alpha briefly into root — on thin alpha pools (mcap < 1000τ) slippage can cost more than the lift in a quarter, flag this; (g) single-validator concentration is its own risk axis — > 60% of staked TAO across all positions held by one validator is a single point of operational failure regardless of APY. Appended into KB_TEXT after TIME_WINDOW_HEURISTICS and before CATEGORY_HEURISTICS so the model sees: maturity → time-windows → validators → categories. Inference cost on Pollinations is $0; ~120 extra prompt tokens. Non-blocking: deterministic sections, paid PnL flow, free-PnL preview branch and draft PR #1 all untouched.',
