    body:
      'Iter 114. Priority 2 slice — the KB\'s RECOMMENDATION_HEURISTICS already tells the model to recommend MIGRATEs ("swap into <peer>", not abstract reallocate), but no validator-level data was flowing into the user prompt. yieldSection in lib/report.js has been computing delegationOpportunities (positions whose current validator is ≥5pp behind their subnet\'s best, sorted by deltaToBest × alphaTokens) + portfolio-level liftIfOptimised since the validator-yield refactor, but ai-insights.js was only sending weightedApy / best / worst. Result: the model couldn\'t name a validator to switch FROM or TO. This iter pipes both into buildUserPrompt: (a) a portfolio-level "Optimised-case weighted APY: X% (lift +Ypp if every position re-delegated to its subnet\'s best validator)" line, emitted only when liftIfOptimised > 0 to avoid noise on already-optimised books; (b) "Re-delegation opportunities (top 5 by τ/year lift — your validator is materially behind the subnet\'s best)" block with per-position rows: alpha amount, validator name (or first 8 chars of hotkey when unnamed), current APY, subnet-best APY, τ/year lift. Capped at 5 to keep prompt token budget bounded — for a book with 30+ positions this is the long tail anyway. The KB\'s "MIGRATE when..." heuristic now has the concrete data to fire on instead of inferring from vibes. Inference cost still $0 on Pollinations; ~50-150 extra prompt tokens on portfolios with material lift available. Non-blocking: deterministic sections untouched, paid PnL flow untouched, free-PnL preview branch untouched.',
